title: no fail buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine milk, soda, sugar and cinnamon in a large heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Boil to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans, vanilla, butter and butter flavoring.
Beat until candy loses its gloss.
Scrape to one end of the pan.
When it begins to thicken and gets creamy looking, drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Remove from wax paper as soon as the pralines congeal.

title: texas caviar (bean dip)
directions: Process 1 1/2 cans of beans in blender with oil and juice until smooth.
Scrape into bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; chill for at least 3 hours before serving with corn chips.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix liquids with the sugar and stir until sugar dissolves. Pour this over the other ingredients which have been mixed together.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving. This can be added to a lettuce and/or tomato salad or served as a separate side dish.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and molasses.
Mix well.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add alternately with milk to batter, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Bake in thin layers about 1/2-inch thick in 9-inch cake pans for about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: white jello
directions: Mix cold water and gelatine; let stand 5 minutes.
Boil sugar and pineapple 2 minutes.
Add gelatine while hot.
Let cool. Cream the cream cheese.
Add marshmallow cream.
Add pineapple mixture and blend at low speed.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix everything together except soup.
Press into cookie sheet and refrigerate overnight.
In morning cut into squares, roll in flour and brown in frying pan.
Put in roaster and pour undiluted soup over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mirliton pie
directions: Blend in bowl the sugar, Bisquick, milk, vanilla, butter and 1 egg at a time.
Then add mirlitons.
Make sure you get water out of mirlitons.
Beat about 1 minute.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: northwoods red cabbage facsimile
directions: Combine red cabbage and onion in large bowl.
Stir in sugar and set aside to meld flavors.

title: easy chili
directions: After browning hamburger, mix all together and simmer until celery and onions are tender.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix and cook until tender celery, onion, pimentos and butter. Add peas.
In casserole dish, put mixture in bottom.
Put soup (undiluted) over mixture.
Sprinkle almonds and crackers on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: mini ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop ham and onion finely.
Place in bowl.
Add cheese, egg, pepper and mustard.
Stir to combine. Spray mini-muffin pan with vegetable oil spray.
Unroll crescent rolls and press dough into one large rectangle.
Cut rectangle into 24 pieces.
Place dough pieces in
mini muffin pan cups.
Use a tart shaper to form a cup.
Flour tart shaper after each use. Place filling in cup.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: date pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla together.
Mix dates, nuts, flour and baking powder together and then add this to the egg mixture with a fork.
Bake in a 9-inch square pan for 35 minutes or a nice golden brown at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into small squares. Mix with 8 ounces of Cool Whip.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix lime jello, cream cheese, marshmallows and water together and cook over medium heat until marshmallows and cream cheese are melted.
Remove from heat and cool a little while (about 5 minutes).
Add pineapple, mayonnaise and canned milk.
Mix well, then add pecans.
Chill until set, 3 to 4 hours.

title: shrimp hurry curry
directions: In
top part of double boiler, simmer onion
and
curry powder in butter until tender.
Do not brown.
Add frozen soup and
stir until smooth.
Add sour cream and shrimp
and
heat until
hot all
through.
Serve over hot rice and
top
with paprika.
My favorite
likes
shrimp
almost any
way
it's cooked.
This is one of my quickies they have
enjoyed through the years.
I
never serve this one with the traditional curry "boys,"
just
plain. But
chutney,
raisins, grated coconut, chopped green onions, etc., may be used.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies fine.
Mix powdered sugar, butter and cream cheese together.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix up pudding and milk.
Put layer of cookies then cream cheese mixture, cookies and pudding. End with cookies on top; put gummy worms in middle of cake.

title: fruit cake
directions: Note:
Total fruit and nuts is to be about 6 pounds.

title: three bean bake
directions: Don't drain beans or add water to soup.
Mix all together. Season with onion, salt and pepper.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a covered dish.

title: just like fresh cooked green beans
directions: Fry 6 slices of bacon.
Break bacon into pieces and set aside. Put beans, 3 tablespoons grease, onion soup mix and brown sugar into pan.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Add bacon pieces.

title: old timey egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until set and slightly brown.
Add 1/2 cup coconut to mixture before cooking, if desired.

title: green chili enchiladas(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Brown meat.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder as you cook. In a separate large pan, add soup, water and chili.
Bring to a boil.
Turn off heat.
Fry tortillas until tender.
Grate cheese. Chop onion.
Dip 6 tortillas in soup mix.
Place in roasting pan. Sprinkle 1/3 of meat on tortillas, also 1/3 cheese and onion, then repeat until all 2 dozen tortillas are used, ending with cheese.
Bake in oven at 450° until cheese melts.
(Put remaining soup on table if desired or pour over finished enchiladas in pan.)

title: seafood au gratin
directions: Let thicken.
Pour into casserole dish over seafood (I use 1 pound fresh lump crabmeat and 1 1/2 pounds boiled and peeled shrimp).
Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 15 minutes until bubbly.

title: cheese rings
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour and pepper and mix well. Use cookie press to make into desired shapes.
Bake at 400° on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetable and rice primavera
directions: Saute vegetables and onions in butter until tender. Add chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes or until broth is absorbed. Sprinkle with cheese before serving.

title: cheesy chicken crescent dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chicken and 1/3 cup cheese in bowl.
Separate rolls.
Place 3 tablespoons chicken and cheese mixture at wide end of each crescent roll and roll up.
In medium saucepan, combine soup, milk and 1/3 cup cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour 1/2 soup mixture into greased oblong glass dish.
Reserve some soup mixture for sauce.
Arrange crescents over soup mixture in dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top and return to oven 5 to 10 minutes until cheese melts.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: cheesy beef sandwiches
directions: Brown ground meat, cut up cheese. Mix together all ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: rye bread appetizers
directions: Mix together horseradish, mayo, cheese and beef.
Top with black olive slices.
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture on top of bread. Spread evenly on top, then broil until bubbly at 300°.

title: fruit filled muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Stir milk, oil and egg in bowl until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except preserves, and glaze until moistened.
Put batter in baking cups, drop 1 level teaspoon fruit on center of batter in each cup.
Bake 13 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan and drizzle glaze on top.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saut onion, green pepper, mushrooms, celery and stew tomatoes until vegetables are tender.
Combine ground beef and vegetables in a large pan.
Stir in chili powder. Add tomato soup and water and bring to a boil.
Add kidney beans and vinegar.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer for several hours.

title: quesadilla bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients first.
Combine the damp ingredients. Mix all thoroughly, but do not overbeat.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour in an ungreased rectangular baking pan.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir just enough to mix spices.
Cover and set on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: big batch cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in nuts and chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: 12 dozen.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix sugars, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Add cherries and extract.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell and dot with margarine. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° for about 25 more minutes.

title: zucchini lasagna(low-fat)
directions: Slice zucchini lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices.
Dredge in seasoned flour.
Heat small amount of oil in large skillet; brown zucchini.
Drain on paper towel. Combine Ricotta, egg, oregano and 3 tablespoons Parmesan.

title: sour cream peach cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in ungreased, oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) with fork, scraping corners frequently until moistened.
Stir batter vigorously with fork 1 minute.
Scrape sides with rubber spatula.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake until top springs back when touched lightly in center, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Loosen cake from sides.
Cut and serve directly from pan.
Store any remaining cake, loosely covered, in refrigerator.

title: whole wheat dinner rolls
directions: In small saucepan, heat water, shortening and 3 tablespoons sugar until very warm (120° to 130°).
In large bowl blend warm liquid, 2 cups flour, 1 cup whole wheat flour, sugar, salt, yeast and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
By hand stir in remaining wheat flour and enough all-purpose flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl and turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise until double, about 60 minutes.
Grease (not oil) pans.
Punch down dough. Pinch off and shape into balls, place in prepared pans.
Cover and let rise until double, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 375° for about 15 to 20 minutes (golden brown).
Rolls sound hollow when lightly tapped.
Rub tops with butter.

title: bean and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, saute' garlic, onion and bell pepper.
Simmer 5 min, add chili powder and salt.
Add 1 can pinto beans, 1 can tomatoes, 3/4 c. dry rice. Pour into casserole dish, cover and bake 1 hr. at 350°.
The last few minutes top with grated cheese.

title: sand art brownies
directions: Mix. Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef and tomato stir-fry
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut into 1/2 x 1/8 x 2-inch strips. Drain tomatoes;
reserve	liquid.
Combine tomato liquid, soy sauce, ginger, cornstarch and sugar; mix well.
Stir-fry beef in hot
oil in a large skillet or wok over high heat;	remove meat.
Add green pepper and onion to skillet; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Add beef,
stewed
tomatoes
and
tomato
mixture to skillet.
Stir. Cover.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Makes 5 cups.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash and trim off ends of zucchini; cook in microwave 7 minutes.
Cut in half lengthwise; scoop out the centers and chop. Cook sausage, onion and celery until meat is done; drain.
Stir in croutons, 1/2 the cheese and the chopped zucchini.
Mound mixture in zucchini shells.
Microwave on High 5 minutes (turn halfway through cooking time).
Top with remaining cheese and microwave 1 minute.

title: blueberry square
directions: Mix
cracker crumbs, oleo, confectioners sugar and nuts together
and
press
in
x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar,
eggs
and lemon juice together with mixer; pour on pie crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add blueberry pie filling.

title: italian kish
directions: Cook ground sausage or diced ham (cook's choice).
Mix with egg mixture.
Pour in pie pan and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: You will need 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: cocoa syrup
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a medium saucepan; gradually stir in water until mixture is smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into container, cool, cover and refrigerate.
Use to prepare cold drinks (add 1 to 2 tablespoons cocoa syrup to an 8 ounce glass cold milk and stir until blended).
Yield:
2 cups syrup.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Stir well. Gradually stir in bread.
Add brown sugar and raisins.
Pour mixture into 8 x 11 1/3-inch casserole dish.
Place dish in cake pan and add water in cake pan, halfway up dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: beet pickle
directions: Cook your beets, peel and cut as desired.
Bring the vinegar and spices to a boil.
Add beets and let them come to a boil.
Put in glass jars; pour vinegar mixture over them.
Seal.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: hot corned-beef barbecues
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in skillet; add cayenne pepper to taste.
Stir ketchup into seasonings.
Stir water in ketchup.
Stir in corned beef; break up with wooden spoon.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes or until most of liquid has evaporated and corned beef mixture is thick.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in buttermilk for 30 minutes.
Mix margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add egg yolks and flavorings and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately.
Fold in stiff egg whites.
Grease Bundt pan well.
Put small amount of batter in pan and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Add more batter and sprinkle cinnamon mixture on top.
Dot with margarine. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool
10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: midwest vegetable crunch salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except the bacon bits.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: blueberry sour cream cake
directions: Coat berries with 1/3 cup flour.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat eggs; fold in sour cream.
Combine remaining 1 2/3 cups flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture, then lightly fold in berries.
Turn into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done when tested.
Remove from pan and cool on rack. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook rice according to directions and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cut chicken in bite size pieces and saute in skillet. Mix soup, sour cream, almonds and chicken. Spread over rice mixture. Crush Ritz crackers. Melt margarine and mix with crackers. Stir in poppy seeds; spread on top of chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in egg yolks and enough water to make a stiff dough.
Knead it on a floured board for 1 minute.
Roll out dough until thin.
Cut into strips with a pizza cutter.
Drop noodles into 2 quarts boiling chicken broth; cook until tender.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: lebanese white cheese
directions: In a heavy saucepan heat the milk to about 90° (dip baby finger in milk until you can withstand a count to 10). Dissolve 1 cheese tablet in 1 ounce warm water.
Stir into milk and cover. Cover with a blanket and let rest 1 1/2 hours.
Place cheese cloth into strainer and pour milk mixture in gently.
Mold cheese into hand sized balls. Sprinkle with salt and place in container with 7 ice cubes.
Allow to cool and then refrigerate.

title: baked catfish dijon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange fish in shallow baking dish. Salt and pepper liberally; cover with sliced onion and dot with butter.
Bake for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard, vermouth and Tabasco.
Pour over fish and broil 2 to 3 minutes, until brown and bubbly.
Sprinkle parsley over top of finished dish.
Serve hot with lemon wedges.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Dice ingredients into small pieces.
Add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Squeeze limes over salad and mix.
Makes about one quart.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep in fridge 3 to 4 weeks.

title: no-crumble meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup tomato juice to pour on top after meat is packed in a 4 1/2-inch ungreased loaf pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Place all ingredients except soup in a greased baking dish in layers. Pour soup over ingredients and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Lightly butter 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook celery and onion in small amount of water until tender.
Drain.
Mix vegetables, onion, celery, mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread cracker crumbs over top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Mix flour and oil together.
Add onion, bell pepper, cook until tender (not browned).
Add tomatoes and cook 20-30 minutes.
Add water, pepper, sugar, salt.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Good over country steak or veal.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems (save).
Dip caps in melted oleo. Place upside down in casserole.
Chop stems.
Saute with onion and garlic in oleo 10 minutes.
Add spinach, meats and seasonings. Fill caps with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven 15 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with Marshmallow Creme.
Stir in nuts.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Cut the vegetables such as green peppers, round onions, carrots, celery, cauliflower, daikon (turnips) and cucumbers lengthwise.
Pour the boiling water into a mixture of vinegar, sugar and salt.
Cool and pour over vegetables in a jar.

title: pineapple crush
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Mix until ice is crushed.
Pour into cups.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and add chopped onion.
Place beef mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Add frozen vegetables.
Mix cream of chicken soup with enough milk to pour over vegetables.
Layer with cheese.
Top with tater tots.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.

title: borsch
directions: Place stock, vegetables and seasonings in soup kettle.

Bring to a boil; reduce heat, then cover and simmer 45 minutes. Saute chopped onion in oil until golden; remove from heat and add honey, vinegar, tomato and Tamari. Stir mixture into soup. Garnish soup with sour cream or plain yogurt; serve with dark rye bread. Yields 2 1/2 to 3 quarts. Best made a few hours in advance.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in boiling water until tender.
Add butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat and serve at once.
Crisp bits of bacon or ham give a good flavor to soup.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl, spread mixture onto tortilla shells but do not spread to the end of the shells.
Roll shells up and stick a toothpick into shells to hold together.
Let sit in refrigerator over night or until firm.
When you are ready to serve, slice the rolls.

title: cream toast
directions: In medium saucepan, mix flour with melted margarine.
Add milk.
Stir in shredded sharp Cheddar cheese until thickened. Serve over toast.

title: bean sprout tuna chow mein
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water.
Add soy sauce.
Stir in cornstarch.
Heat oil in wok over high heat.
When hot, toss in celery and onions.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add bamboo shoots, mushrooms and bean sprouts.
Stir bouillon mixture and add to vegetables.
Add tuna, stir and cook until hot and sauce is clear. Serve over hot rice.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add fruit cocktail and egg and beat until smooth.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch Pyrex pan.
Let cool partially and cut into squares before putting on topping.

title: butterscotch spectacular
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter.
Put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip until smooth.
Pour this onto cooled crust. Mix pudding with milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Put remaining Cool Whip on top of this and sprinkle with nuts.

title: homemade summer sausage
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients well (use hands if necessary).
Roll into 2 to 3 rolls as firmly as possible.
Place on aluminum foil; put shiny side next to meat.
Wrap so seam side is up. Allow to stand in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
Punch holes in bottom of rolls.
Place on rack in pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Chill before slicing.
Very good!

title: easy peach upside-down cake
directions: Spread brown sugar on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chop peaches and put on top of brown sugar; sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Mix cake according to package directions, except use reserved peach juice instead of water.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake springs back when touched.

title: frozen peach punch
directions: Dissolve jello into boiling water; set aside.
In another bowl, dissolve sugar in 4 cups of water.
Add jello mixture to this, then add peach Hi-C and pineapple juice.
Mix all together and freeze in milk cartons or large plastic containers.

title: french silk chocolate
directions: Cream the butter; gradually add 3/4 cup of sugar, cream well. Blend in 1 square (1 ounce) chocolate, melted and cooled.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each egg.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Top with whipped cream and nuts.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Let ice cream and cool whip thaw and soften.
Mix together in a large bowl until well blended.
Pour into crust and freeze for approximately 2 - 3 hours until firm.
Crush cookies and sprinkle on top of pie.
Slice and serve immediately.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased and floured loaf or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
(If using plain cake mix add 1 small box vanilla instant pudding.)

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: *Save some cheese for sprinkling on top of casserole.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Mix all together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix oil, Worcestershire and garlic salt.
Mix cereals, nuts and pretzels, then mix all together.
Bake 2 hours at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
After first hour, add 3 cups Cheerios.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on the package; set aside to cool. Add carrots, peppers and onion.
Make dressing using all the other ingredients.
Pour over spaghetti and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan in 350° oven.
Remove and add graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well and press evenly into bottom of pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumb mixture. Cover with nuts, coconut and chocolate chips.
Press into pan. Return to oven.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut, cool and remove from pan.

title: baked dijon chicken(low cholesterol; low salt)
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except bread crumbs) in a baking dish.
Add chicken, coating both sides with mixture.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spring garden dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl beat cottage cheese, grated carrot, grated onion, grated green pepper, salt, garlic salt and dash of pepper.
Blend until fairly smooth.
Fold in yogurt or sour cream. Dip for chips or raw vegetables.

title: talerini
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Cook macaroni.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let simmer until cheese is completely melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces. This should take about 2 months. Cover and cook over fire (kerosene) for about 4 weeks at 465°. This will serve 3,800 people. Add the rest of the ingredients.
If more are expected, two rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: tortellini and broccoli
directions: Cook tortellini in boiling water until done.
Place broccoli in colander; break up with fork and hot water.
Pour tortellini (when done) and boiling water over broccoli to drain.
Put mixture in bowl with oil, margarine and garlic powder.
Add grated cheese to taste.

title: chili pie
directions: Grease a pie pan.
Drain chiles and spread on the bottom of the pan.
Cover with the shredded cheese.
Mix the eggs and milk and pour over the cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 23 minutes. Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: kwik-n-easy party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with assorted vegetable dippers.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill. Serve with chips.

title: texas confetti cornbread
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together the first 5 ingredients. In separate bowl, combine eggs, buttermilk and oil; mix well.
Stir liquid mixture into cornmeal mixture, blending well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Divide batter between pans and pour into two well-oiled, preheated 9 x 11-inch baking pans.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
2 (9 x 11-inch) pans cornbread.

title: 15 minute pineapple cake
directions: Combine pineapple with instant vanilla pudding.
Stir well. Add Cool Whip. Frost cake.
You usually have enough filling for 2 or 3 loaf cakes.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Blend cheese and whipped topping; stir in dry jello.
Fold in fruit and pour into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch dish.
Best if made the day before.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: elsie's apple tarts
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; set aside until bubbly. Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter as for pie dough.
Add egg yolks to yeast mixture and add to flour and butter mixture.
Roll dough out thin; cut in squares and put in about 3 slices of apple.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar, a dab of flour and dot with butter.
Fold dough over apples and pinch edges to seal.
Put in greased pans and let rise about 35 minutes.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes in center rack of oven until lightly browned.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Pour cherries in bottom of loaf pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over the cherries.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over mix.
Pour butter over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk, egg and apple slices.
Fry in 1/2-inch oil at 350°, turning when browned on one side.

title: quick seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Mix well together. Chill 1/2 hour. Yields 2 2/3 cups.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Melt butter.
Dip chicken in the melted butter and then roll in the cracker crumbs.
Line baking dish with aluminum foil. Place chicken in pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake for about 45 minutes or an hour at 350°.

title: hash browns
directions: Mix together hash browns, large sour cream, Cheddar cheese soup (undiluted), cream of celery soup (undiluted) and small amount of minced onion.
Pour into rectangular baking dish; sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 400°.

title: ham and potato scallop(microwave)
directions: Pour milk into 2 cup glass measure.
Cook on 70° for 2 minutes; set aside.
Place butter in 2 cup glass measure.
Cook on High for 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Cook on High for 30 seconds. Briskly stir in hot milk, mustard, salt and pepper into butter. Set aside.

title: white chicken and spaghetti
directions: Stew fryer until tender and debone in bite size pieces. Reserve broth.
Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in margarine about 5 minutes, until tender.
Add soups and pimentos.
Simmer until hot.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Cook spaghetti in broth until tender.
Pour sauce over spaghetti and mix.
Heat well before serving.

title: souped up bread
directions: Slice bread vertically but not completely to the bottom of loaf.
Place bread on enough foil to cover.
Pour soup over top of bread.
Layer onions and cheese over top of soup.
Cover and seal seams in foil.
You may want to bake bread on baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Pack into loaf pan. Combine last 4 ingredients and mix well.
Pour over meat loaf and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients with raisins, nuts or dates.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: taco casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook ground beef and onion until beef is browned; drain off excess fat.
Stir tomato sauce, water and taco mix into meat mixture; heat through.
Remove from heat.
In bowl (big), beat eggs.
Stir in milk and meat mixture.
Stir in beans, cheese and taco shells.
Put all mixture in a large baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes. Top with lettuce, tomatoes and olives.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bisquick cherry swirl coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients, except pie filling and Glaze. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Spread 2/3 of the batter in the bottom of the baking dish.
Spread pie filling over batter.
(Filling may not completely cover batter.)
Drop remaining batter by tablespoon onto pie filling. Bake until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Drizzle with Glaze while warm.

title: relish
directions: Mix all in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 50 minutes; stirring often.
Remove spice bag.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix Wesson oil and salad dressing; add crackers and mix well. Heat in microwave; stir every 2 minutes for 6 minutes.
Drain on paper towel if necessary.
Serve to square dancers.

title: steak roll
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix bread crumbs, egg, seasoning, onion soup and mushrooms.
Lay steak out flat and spread stuffing mixture on it.
Then roll steak up and tie with string.
Place steak roll in shallow baking dish and cover with foil, shiny side in.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: easy eggplant parmesan
directions: Wash eggplant and then slice into 1/4-inch slices.
(Skin may be peeled if preferred).
Dip each slice into beaten egg, then into lightly salted flour.
Fry in olive oil until light brown on each side and fork inserts easily.
Drain on paper towel, then place in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish in layers -- Mozzarella cheese and tomato sauce on each side of eggplant until all eggplant is used.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 45 minutes at 325° or until cheese melts.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well. Add onions and saute to golden brown.
Add chili powder, chili salsa and tomato sauce. Rinse can with 1/2 can water. Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Add 2/3 cup cooked rice. Simmer a few more minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease (bottom only) of 8 or 9-inch square pan and set aside.
Mix together first 4 dry ingredients and set aside.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking dish. Cook and stir ground beef until brown. Drain.
Mix sour cream, mayo, cheese and onion. Reserve.
Mix Bisquick with water until soft dough forms.
Pat in pan, pressing dough 1/2-inch up the side. Layer the beef, tomatoes and green pepper in pan.
Spoon cream mixture on top. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake until edges of dough are light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Double recipe and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar;
stir in all other ingredients that have been tossed.

title: quick and easy baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish in the order listed.
Toss lightly to mix well. Bake, uncovered, 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Blend in egg.
Spread onto bottom of pastry shell. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Cool.
Brush with maple syrup and garnish with pecan halves, if desired.

title: linda's chicken salad
directions: In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, salt, pepper, mustard, sugar and vinegar.
In large bowl, sprinkle apple cubes with 1 teaspoon lemon juice; toss.
Add chicken, celery, grapes, pecans and dressing.
Refrigerate.
Arrange on salad plates; garnish with grapes and apple wedges dipped in lemon juice.
Serves 6.

title: asparagus and turkey quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bring 2 quarts of water to boil.
Add plum tomatoes for 1 minute, remove to colander and refresh under cold water.
Peel tomatoes, chop and set aside.
Blanch asparagus in same water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Refresh under cold water; set aside.
Heat olive oil in saute pan until hot.
Add garlic and tomato; saute for 2 minutes.
Season well with salt and pepper. Remove from heat; set aside.

title: homemade sausage
directions: Mix seasonings and hamburger.
Knead well and refrigerate for 4 days.
Each day, take out and knead and return to refrigerator.
On 4th day, knead and shape mixture into 4 rolls.
Place on rack and bake at 140° for 8 hours.
Turn every 2 hours, then enjoy.

title: classic chess pie
directions: Stir together sugar and next 7 ingredients until blended. Add eggs, stirring well. Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, shielding edges of crust with aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning. Cool completely on wire rack.

title: onion twist
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in dip mix.
Cut in butter until mixture forms fine crumbs. Sprinkle cold water over top, a tablespoon at a time, mixing lightly until pastry holds together.
Roll out on a lightly floured cloth to a rectangle.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Lift and twist strips.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until lightly golden.
Remove from cookie sheets.

title: virginia pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs (slightly beaten).
Add flour and milk (alternately), beating after each addition.
Add 1 teaspoon baking powder to the last cup of flour, stirring in the flavorings.
Baking in a well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan, bake 45 minutes at 200°, then increase heat to 350° and bake until done, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
When done, cake will leave tester clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes; turn out.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Place in glass bowl.
Mix in green pepper and onion with beans.
Combine seasonings and rest of ingredients. Pour over mixture and stir.
Let set overnight!

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes in small casserole dish. Serve with wheat thins.

title: quick mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add taco seasoning and corn.
Mix together warm soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix condensed milk with water to make 1 quart.
Add sugar and rice.
Bake at 350°
for 1` 1/2 hours; stir every 15 minutes.

title: johnny soup
directions: Brown the sausage and onion. Drain fat.
Add tomatoes and broth.
Season with oregano. Boil for 15 minutes. Add noodles. Cook for 12 to 15 minutes until noodles are done.

title: english almond taffy
directions: Chop nuts fine.
In a heavy pan, cook butter and sugar.
Cook and stir until dark tan (also can see a little smoke coming up). Pour onto two 12 x 24-inch buttered cookie sheets.
Spread evenly. Pour over each pan 1 pound chocolate chips, spread evenly. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cut up after chocolate is very hard.
(Very hard to cut.)

title: nana clark's spice cake
directions: *To sour milk, add 1 1/2 tablespoons vinegar to milk and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Simmer chicken, covered with water (salt and pepper) 30 to 45 minutes until tender.
Drain and chill.
Remove bones.
Slice each breast into 3 pieces lengthwise.

title: beef tenderloin extraordinaire
directions: Mix ingredients; rub on tenderloin.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Put on rack inside pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Adjust time for preferred doneness.
Let set 10 minutes after removing from oven.
Serve with Knorr hunter sauce.

title: rock candy
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water and stir until it boils to a hard crack stage.
Remove from heat.
Add food coloring and flavoring.
Pour onto a powdered sugar foil.
Crack when cool.

title: chicken chili with beans
directions: Put chicken breasts in Dutch oven or big pot.
Cover with water; boil 15 minutes.
Take chicken pieces out and cool.

title: simple frosting
directions: Using mixer on low speed, mix all ingredients, mixing well, then beat on high speed.
The longer it beats, the fluffier it gets.
You may add what flavoring you like.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Put hominy and meat in dish.
Cook soups, cheese and hot sauce over low heat stirring constantly until soups are hot and cheese melts.
Pour over hominy and meat.
Cover with Fritos or Doritos, crushed.
Put in 350° oven and heat until bubbles.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add all other ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat for a few minutes.
Add 3/4 chocolate chips to mix.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Sprinkle rest of chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.

title: sharon's rocky road bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Microwave 1 cup morsels in medium microwave-safe bowl on High for 1 minute. Stir. Microwave at additional 10 second intervals. Stir until smooth. Cool to room temperature. Combine flour and baking powder in small bowl. Beat sugar, butter and vanilla in large bowl until crumbly. Beat in eggs. Add melted chocolate. Beat until smooth. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Spread batter into prepared baking pan. Bake for 16 to 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out slightly sticky. Remove from oven. Sprinkle immediately with marshmallows, nuts and remaining chocolate morsels. Return to oven for 2 minutes.

title: ma's christmas bread
directions: Sift together the flour, powder, sugar and salt.
Add fruit and nuts.
Beat eggs and combine with milk and melted butter.
Add this to the flour mixture, stirring just enough to moisten the flour.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan and let stand for 30 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: orange jello delight
directions: Add 3 cups boiling water to jello; mix well.
Add orange juice concentrate.
Add drained pineapple and oranges; mix.
Put in refrigerator and let set up.
Mix pudding (dry) with Cool Whip. Spread on top of set up jello.
Sprinkle with Cheddar Cheese.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and season to taste.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Blend together sour cream, cream cheese, cottage cheese and chives.

title: skinny dip
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly in a mixing bowl. Chill several hours. Serve with crisp raw vegetables. Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pat flour and water in a bowl and stir it.
Then you roll it with a rolling pin.
Slice the dough.
After you slice it, you put it in a pot.
You cook it for 1 hour.
When it's all finished, you put it on the table in a big bowl and people eat them. This is my favorite.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; slice onion thin into rings.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Put in covered dish and refrigerate for about 3 hours.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Do not use mixer.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lemon lime salad
directions: Melt jello in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add pineapple and condensed milk.
Add cream cheese.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels, water and butter.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over low heat.
Dip turtles in chocolate mixture and refrigerate for a few minutes.

title: dill rolls
directions: Season steaks with salt and pepper.
Spread one side of each steak with mustard.
Place pickle on each steak.
Roll up steaks and fasten with wooden toothpicks.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream all together.
Bake at 400° for the first 15 minutes, then at 375° until done.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs separately.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° in 3 round 9-inch cake pans until done. Cool.

title: shrimply divine dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and sugar. Bring to boil. Pour over bean mixture. Let set overnight.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Arrange cherry pie mix in shallow baking dish.
Combine sugar, oatmeal, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; pour over cherry pie mix. Then pour softened margarine over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: no cook candy balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Shape into 2-inch size balls.
Roll each in coconut and chill.
Makes about 30 balls.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Layer the vegetables in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine the sugar, salt, pepper, garlic powder and Accent; sprinkle dry ingredients over each layer.
Put Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
This is great; it resembles a pizza taste.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix together in pan and cook over medium heat until thick. Put in baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: red rice
directions: Brown meat slightly in the bacon drippings.
Combine all other ingredients, mix well.
Bake in covered casserole dish at 350° for one hour.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Combine cranberries and 1/2 cup sugar.
Sift flour, salt, soda and remaining sugar.
Mix egg, buttermilk and butter; add to dry ingredients, mixing just enough to moisten.
Add cranberries, mixing slightly.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook peas and carrots according to package directions; drain. In a saucepan, cook onion and mushrooms in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour, salt, sage and pepper.
Add water, milk and chicken bouillon granules, all at once.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in drained cooked vegetables, chicken or turkey, pimento and parsley; heat until bubbly.

title: easy icing
directions: Blend butter, Crisco and sugar.
Gradually add milk and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Drain and cool.
Mix all other
ingredients	with rice.
Refrigerate.
(Can be made up day before.)

title: cucumber soup
directions: Simmer cucumber and onions for 20 minutes in just enough water to cover.
Pour into blender.
Add mashed potatoes.
Blend well. Add chicken broth and milk while motor is going.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill or serve hot.

title: easy fried apple pies
directions: Get a pastry sheet and flour.
Open canned biscuits and take out 1 biscuit.
Place on pastry sheet and roll out with rolling pin into a 6-inch circle.
Place 2 tablespoons applesauce on biscuit.
Place 1/2 to 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon on applesauce.
Fold over and use a fork to press edges together. Heat iron skillet on medium with 2 tablespoons butter flavored Crisco.
When hot, place pie in skillet until browned on both sides.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place bread cubes in bottom of pan. Cook sausage until crumbled and drain.
Cover bread with sausage, grated cheese and chopped onion.
Mix milk, eggs and dry mustard. Pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes and uncover for last 15 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lemon butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together flour, butter and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar until well blended.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly golden.

title: spicy breakfast casserole
directions: Combine eggs and seasoning. Place sausage in a 1/2-quart baking dish. Pour egg mixture over sausage. Sprinkle with chilies, then cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar (beat well).
Add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add flour.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Start in cold oven.
Do not open door until time is up.

title: huckleberry or blueberry pie
directions: Bake sweet potatoes until tender, peel and mash.
Make sure all lumps are removed, straining if necessary.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) 50 minutes or until a silver knife inserted in filling 1-inch from edge of pie comes out clean.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Wash large head fresh broccoli and dry thoroughly.
Cut into very small pieces.
Peel stalks of broccoli and cut into small pieces also.
Slice 1 sweet onion and add 8 ounces grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix with dressing.
Refrigerate overnight.
Crumble bacon on top just before serving.

title: apple delight(this is a good apple recipe.)
directions: In a large bowl, sift the flour with the sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg yolk and milk; mix well.
Divide into two balls.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface and place one in a large baking dish.
Cover with apples and corn flakes.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar mixture on top of apples.
Place other rolled dough on top.
Beat egg white and put over crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour glaze on top.

title: granola bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line a 15 x 10-inch pan with aluminum foil; grease foil.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients well. Press evenly into pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool slightly; remove from pan and remove foil.
Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.
(May substitute items for chocolate chips, coconut, etc.)
Makes 48 bars.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix together flour and milk; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat shortening, margarine, sugar and vanilla at high speed until creamy, about 5 minutes.
Add the cooled mixture and beat until fluffy.

title: sweet and sour dogs
directions: Depending on amount desired.

title: hot roll wheat batter bread
directions: In large bowl, combine flour mixture with yeast from foil packet and wheat germ; mix well.
Stir in hot water, molasses, oil and egg until well mixed (batter will be sticky).
Cover; let dough rise in bowl 30 minutes, or until light and doubled in size, on wire rack set over large pan to which hot water has been added. Grease 2-quart casserole.
Stir down dough; spread in prepared casserole.
Cover; let rise over hot water 30 minutes or until light and doubled in size.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Immediately remove from casserole.
Yields 1 (16 slice) loaf.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, chips and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast with rice
directions: Pour uncooked rice in baking dish.
Slice onion.
Place on the rice.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice and onion.
Pour mushroom soup and water over this.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: baked peanut butter popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in roasting pan.
In heavy saucepan, stir together sugar and syrup.
Stir constantly.
Cook until mixture boils.
Stir in peanut butter.
Cook without stirring 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour peanut butter mixture over popcorn.
Stir to coat well.
Bake in 250° oven, stirring occasionally, 1 hour.
Cool stirring some to break apart.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until smooth and looks like scrambled eggs, not thick.
Add onions and cream cheese.
Refrigerate before serving.
Good on chips or crackers.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Heat frypan or griddle to 325° or 330°.
In a large bowl, sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add the butter or margarine to flour mixture and mix as for a pie crust.
Add currants and raisins.
Beat the eggs with the milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well with your hands.
If the dough is sticky, add more flour.
Roll out on a lightly floured board and cut with a cookie cutter or a glass.

title: tropical spread
directions: Chill overnight before serving. Serve with Wheat Thins or assorted crackers.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: hot christmas drink
directions: Melt cinnamon red hots in water, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Cut cake horizontally, making 3 layers.
Sprinkle evenly with liqueur, then cut cake into 1-inch cubes.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on package for pudding.
Layer 1/2 the cake cubes, pudding and strawberries and 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping in a 6-cup serving bowl.
Repeat cake, pudding and berry layers and garnish with remaining topping.
Chill.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Stir together and let boil 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and let cool.
Beat.
Pour into a buttered dish.

title: crock-pot express
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 3 hours or on low all day.
Serve over cooked rice or mashed or cubed potatoes. Very easy and tasty.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Chill punch and ginger ale until ready to serve.
Add ginger ale and serve ice cold.

title: posole hominy and chiles
directions: Drain and rinse hominy.
Butter a 3-quart casserole.
Divide hominy into 3 portions.

Layer 1 portion in bottom of casserole. Dot with sour cream and margarine and season with salt and pepper. Add a layer of 1/2 of the green chiles and green onions, which have been sauteed in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Repeat layers, ending with hominy on top.
Dot with sour cream and cover with grated cheeses.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook noodles. Once noodles have cooled, add all ingredients; mix, then pour in salad dressing. Chill overnight.

title: fast summer salad
directions: Thaw under cold water.
Add pasta twists and Parmesan cheese (or whatever you like).
Toss with Good Seasons Italian salad dressing.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Pour over remaining ingredients; marinate overnight.
Serves 15.

title: cajun meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a heavy medium skillet over medium-low heat.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, cayenne pepper, thyme, cumin and pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently, about 10 minutes.

title: rolled fillet of sole
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese and onion on each fillet.
Roll, jelly roll style; secure with a toothpick. Dip each roll in egg and water wash.
Coat with bread crumbs. Place in a well buttered glass dish (11 x 7-inch).
Pour melted butter over top; bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: schnitzer's play dough(not for human consumption)
directions: Mix in a pan the flour, alum and salt.
Add water, oil and food coloring.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until the dough is the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Remove from heat.
Knead a little.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, oil, lemon, vanilla, eggs and salt.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, pecans and apples.
Mix lightly.
Pour into a greased and floured 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Combine powdered sugar and milk, adding more milk until glaze is of proper consistency. Drizzle over cooled cake; sprinkle with nuts.
Store in a covered container.
Makes 12 servings.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slip out yolks; mash with fork.
Mix in salt, pepper and mustard and add salad dressing and vinegar.
Refill whites with egg mixture, heaping it up slightly.

title: virginia's spinach casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and chill thoroughly.
Place in a lightly greased baking dish.
May sprinkle small amount of shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm, then add onion rings and brown.

title: vermont maple syrup fudge
directions: Combine maple syrup, corn syrup and cream in 2-quart heavy saucepan and place over low heat.
Stir constantly, until mixture begins to boil; continue cooking, without stirring, to the soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm (110°) without stirring or beating.

title: strawberry pie(serves 6)
directions: Mix the sugar, cornstarch and water and cook until thick.
Add jello.
Stir well.
Place strawberries in pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature and mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until mixture will hold shape of a ball easily.
Shape and roll in parsley, paprika or chopped pecans. Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Chill:
milk, pineapple, cherry pie filling and Cool Whip. Chill well.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours.

title: old fashioned string beans
directions: Place string beans in heavy pot with plenty of water or bean juice from canned beans. Add salt, pepper, sugar and bacon drippings to taste. Add cut up, peeled potatoes if desired. Boil and cook down until beans start to shrivel up. Turn down heat and simmer until done like you want them. This will take a couple of hours. Be sure to add more water if necessary.

title: crisp topping for fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add whole egg to dry mixture and mix with fork or fingers until crumbly. Pour over any fruit in season.
Pour melted butter over mixture. Bake at 350° until done (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Note:
This may be used with most any fruit.
If fruit is really tart, add 1/2 c. sugar to fruit.

title: gala pecan spread
directions: Combine cheese and milk, mixing well.
Stir in dried beef, green pepper, onion flakes and seasoning; mix well.
Fold in sour cream.
Spoon into 8-inch pie plate.
Heat and crisp the pecans in butter with salt.
Sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and pepper in bowl.
Combine all other ingredients together and boil 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Then pour over cabbage mixture.
Stir and chill overnight.
Lasts 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together Crisco, flour, eggs and both sugars.
Add remaining ingredients mixing well.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets.
Make cookies with a tablespoon measuring spoon.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: smothered burritos
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco sauce and jalapeno.
Roll hamburger and small amount of cheese in tortillas.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat soup, green chilies and water in saucepan, then pour over tortillas and sprinkle remaining cheese over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: a very good salad
directions: Mix pineapple, oranges and cherries.
Mix the vanilla instant pudding into the fruit.
Let set for 4 to 8 hours or overnight. Before serving, cut bananas into slices and add to mixture.

title: port wine gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, add pineapple and cranberry sauce. Stir; add nuts and wine.
Let set in mold.
Soften cream cheese and mix with sour cream.
Beat until smooth then spread on top of set gelatin mold.
When ready to serve, remove from mold and garnish with lettuce.

title: chili-burger supper
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain thoroughly. Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
Add drained macaroni, chili-beef soup and tomato soup.
Heat, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 6 minutes, until bubbly.
Cut cheese slices in half diagonally.
Place cheese triangles on the hot mixture. Cover for a few minutes to allow cheese to melt slightly.

title: marilyn's fruit cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Mix really well.
Put candied fruit and nuts in bowl and mix with flour.
Pour first 4 ingredients into the fruit mixture, working with your hands.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours or until knife comes out clean.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole pan. Combine chicken, cheese, beans and spices in a large bowl; blend well.
To prepare crust, combine flour, milk and butter; blend well.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: me-ma's refrigerator rolls
directions: In the 2 cups hot water, add salt, shortening and sugar.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast.
Add to first mixture.
Add beaten eggs. Mix well.
Beat in flour.
Let rise in refrigerator.
Set out before baking until brown on top at 350°.

title: light and easy lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet with oil, cook chicken until tender and brown on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Combine soup and milk; stir in lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Top each chicken piece with lemon slice.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until fork-tender, stirring once.
Serves 5.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Will not work with dried herbs.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Heat sugar, butter and evaporated milk in a heavy saucepan, over medium heat, until mixture boils.
Continue to boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Cool.
Yields 5 pounds.

title: easy banana cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy french bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix yeast, water, salt and sugar.
Add 5 cups flour, mix with mixer on low speed for 5 minutes.
Add enough flour to make dough elastic, flour board, fold out on board and knead for 5 minutes.
Grease large bowl, place dough in and cover.
Set in warm place until dough doubles in size, about 1 hour.
Fold out on floured board and knead again 2 minutes. Place back in bowl to rise again.
Let rise 10 minutes. Gently put back on board and divide into 2 parts.
Place one back in bowl.
Leave one on board.
Let stand (covered 10 minutes).
One at a time gently roll out 8 x 10-inch and hand roll up into loaf.
Grease pans (2) and sprinkle with corn meal.
Place loaf in pan.
Repeat for second loaf.
Slice crosswise (4 to 6 slices) 1/2 inch deep. Brush with egg white mixture.
Bake 20 minutes and brush with egg whites again.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.

title: raspberry almond muffins
directions: Cut almond paste into 12 pieces and pat each piece into a round disk.
Beat butter until creamy.
Beat in sugar until pale. Beat in eggs, one at a time, then mix in baking powder, baking soda and almond extract.
Fold in 1 cup flour, then buttermilk and 1 cup flour.
Spoon 2 tablespoons batter into each cup.
Top with level teaspoon of preserves, then piece of almond paste.
Top with another 2 tablespoons batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 12.

title: cajun hot dish
directions: In a large skillet, saute sausage and onion until sausage is lightly browned. Add corn; cook and stir for 1 minute. Stir in the beans, V-8 juice, paprika, cumin and cayenne, if desired. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 3 minutes. Stir in the rice. Remove from the heat; cover and let stand for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese. Yield: 4 servings.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine.
If freezing, do not make slits in top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut layer cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure, add baking powder and salt and sift together three times.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating very thoroughly after each.
Add flour, alternately with milk, a small amount at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Bake in two greased 9-inch layer pans in moderate oven (375°) 25 to 30 minutes.
Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Use coconut frosting.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine together.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini-walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
In large bowl of electric mixer, at high speed, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick and light.
Fold in grated zucchini.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Gradually add to egg mixture until blended.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Spoon into pans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes in pan, then invert onto wire rack.

title: playdough
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a medium size pot.
Add food coloring to water and stir into pot.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir until it gets to be a globby mess (3 to 5 minutes).
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: lasagna
directions: Bring 4 quarts water and 2 teaspoons salt to rapid boil.
Add lasagna noodles.
Stir to separate them.
Boil 15 minutes; drain and rinse with cold water.

title: hopping john
directions: Soak peas overnight in water to cover.
Strain off water.
Add bacon pieces, onions, salt and chili powder to peas.
Cover with water and simmer 90 minutes.
Then add rice and black pepper and simmer for 20 more minutes.

title: danish puff
directions: Cut 1/2 cup shortening into 1 cup flour.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Divide dough in half; spread into 2 loaves on cookie sheet.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and mix in all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in butter.
Add rest of ingredients except franks.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Prick skins of franks with a fork; place in sauce, cover and cook slowly until heated thoroughly.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: Mix together and heat in double boiler.
Makes 12 cups.

title: apple milkshake
directions: Peel, core and quarter 1 apple.
Chop in blender. Add cinnamon, sweetener, skim milk and water.
Blend in 8 ice cubes, one at a time.

title: baked pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place cooked pasta in 13x9 inch pan.
In skillet combine ground beef, garlic and onion, cooking until ground beef is no longer pink.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomatoes.
Spread this mixture over cooked pasta in pan.
Bake one hour.
Top with mozzarella cheese and bake fifteen more minutes or until bubbly on top.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Bring sugar and pineapple to boil.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add water and congeal partially.
Add cheese, then fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: pineapple pork
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Cook pork in hot oil in a large skillet until browned; drain.
Add onion and cook until tender. Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a small bowl.
Gradually add water, stirring until smooth.
Stir in pineapple juice, vinegar, catsup and soy sauce.
Add to pork, stirring constantly; cook over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Stir in the pineapple and green pepper; cover and cook 3 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: club sandwiches
directions: For each sandwich:
Top first slice of toast with lettuce and cold chicken slice.
Add mayonnaise, if desired.
Top with second toast slice.
Add tomato slice and bacon strips.
Top with third slice of toast.
Peg with 4 toothpicks.
Cut in quarters diagonally.
Serve with sandwiches, point up.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix all ingredients and bake for one hour.
Turn out and stick top a few times with a fork.
While cake is still warm, mix 1 cup confectioners sugar and 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Pour slowly over warm cake.

title: lentil hamburger soup
directions: Crumble meat in 3-quart casserole. Add carrots, onion and garlic.
Cover loosely.

Microwave on High 4 minutes. Stir, cover and microwave 3 to 4 minutes more. Drain. Stir in 2 cups hot water, tomatoes with liquid, mushrooms with liquid and remaining ingredients except 1 cup hot water. Cover tightly and microwave on High, stirring every 6 minutes, until vegetables are tender, 24 to 28 minutes. Stir in 1 cup hot water.
Cover tightly and microwave on High until bubbly, 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and quarter the potatoes.
Cover with water and add 1 teaspoon of salt.
Cook until tender.
Boil eggs.
Let cool, then mash eggs.
When potatoes are done, drain water.
Add mashed eggs, onion, bell pepper, celery, sweet pickle relish, 1 cup of mayonnaise, 3 tablespoons of mustard, 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of pepper.
Mix well and chill.

title: green beans with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a baking dish.
Place beans in baking dish; season with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup cheese, 1 tablespoon butter and cream.
Stir until mixed well.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese and dot with remaining butter.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: hot grog
directions: Stir the apple juice into the milk and water.
Beat the egg whites until soft peaks.
Stir into liquid mixture and heat until warm.
Do not boil.
Use a large pot.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts. Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: wiener bean bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish or bean pot.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown meat.
Add garlic salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce. Set aside.

Mix sour cream, onion and cream cheese well. Layer 1/3 noodles, 1/3 cheese mixture and 1/3 hamburger mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish. Repeat layers. Sprinkle grated cheese over top. Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter and saute garlic, onion and celery for about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and all seasonings, except parsley.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes.
Add parsley.
Serve over cooked rice at once.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in water until almost done.
Then add corn, green beans, peas and corned beef.
Cook until done to taste. Then add 2 tablespoons lard and salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer approximately 5 minutes.

title: congealed ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold in remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ice cream kolacky
directions: Blend 1 cup flour with sugar. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Add ice cream and blend well.
Mixture may firm up because of the ice cream; if so, blend with wooden spoon or electric mixer to form dough.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
With remaining tablespoon of flour, lightly flour board. Remove half of the dough from refrigerator. Roll to 1/4-inch thick. Cut into 3-inch rounds.
Make a fingerprint in center and place a teaspoon of jam.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain grease.
Roll crescent rolls out in baking dish; press seams together.
Spread sausage over crescent rolls. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs and milk together; pour over mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes until set.

title: mocha mix
directions: Put a couple tablespoons of mixture in a cup of hot water. Use more or less according to your own taste.
Makes 1 cup.

title: italian lasagna
directions: Brown
the
meat
in
olive
oil
and
combine with the tomatoes,
tomato paste, parsley, garlic, basil and onion in a large
saucepan
and
let
simmer
for
minutes.
Cook the package
of noodles as directed;
drain, rinse and drain again so it will not stick together.
Put several spoonfuls of sauce in bottom of a large baking dish, then layer noodles, half of the Ricotta
cheese, 1/3 of the Mozzarella cheese and half of the Parmesan cheese.
Repeat again using half of the remaining noodles.
Repeat
again,
ending
up
with sauce and remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes and let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add all the other ingredients together and heat in large saucepan.
Then add hamburger and onion.
Cook lasagna noodles while doing this.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish layer:
1 layer of sauce, 1 layer of cheese and 1 layer of noodles.
Repeat.
End with sauce then cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until hot.
Serve hot with Wheat Thins crackers.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil. Add chopped onion, crushed garlic, fresh rosemary and the juice of one lemon.
Leave the whole lemon in skillet.
Cover and cook until done.
Remove lemon and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: tony's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl; beat at medium speed until well blended. Add egg and mix. Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Mix in cream mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by tablespoon on baking sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crispy cookies. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet. Remove to newspaper to cool completely, then have some milk and warm cookies.

title: susan's macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni as label directs.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
Put half of this in bottom of casserole dish.
Save other for top.
Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Then top with remainder of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening until crumbly.

title: toll house pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Fold in fruits and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over this.
Spoon remaining gelatin over sour cream.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: "frozen waldorf salad"
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine pineapple juice, eggs, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Cool.
Fold remaining ingredients into cooked mixture.
Spoon into 8-inch pan.
Freeze. Cut in squares.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese in top of double boiler until smooth.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into mold. Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: e-z pork chops
directions: Put ingredients over chops.
Bake in covered pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly and cover with water.
Soak overnight. Drain and place in a kettle or Dutch oven.
Add salt pork and water; boil 2 minutes.
Cover, lower heat and simmer for 1 hour or until beans are barely tender.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, but not mushy.

title: old-timey chocolate icing
directions: Melt butter, then add the other ingredients.
Stir until sugar dissolves and spread on cake.
If it's too thick, add a little milk.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain pasta according to package directions.
Cook and stir margarine, onion, salt and pepper over medium heat until onion is slightly tender.
(If not using onion, cook until butter is melted completely and stopped bubbling.)
Blend in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat. Stir in cheese until melted.

title: far-east salad
directions: Cook rice in water and cool before adding celery, crab meat and shrimp.
Use enough salt and curry powder to taste.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Green onions may be added for extra flavor.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef, drain and add Prego sauce plus 1/2 cup of water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Put 1/3 of sauce into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a layer of raw noodles.
Make a layer of cottage cheese and then a layer of mozzarella slices.
Repeat layers and end with a layer of meat sauce.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add seven egg yolks and 2 whole eggs.
Save the seven whites for meringue.
Mix egg and sugar mixture well.
Add can of milk and 2 milk cans of water.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture thickens to a thin pudding, remove from heat and add vanilla.
If mixture gets too thick and sometimes it will get like thick cream pie, add some water and cook a little more, stirring well.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar, syrup, molasses and salt. Bring to boil stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar, soda and vanilla. Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Turn into large pan.
Bake at 250 degrees for 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
Break apart and store in airtight container.

title: anadama bread
directions: Stir corn meal slowly into combined hot milk and water.
Add shortening, molasses and salt.
Let stand until lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast into warm water.
Stir into corn meal mixture alternately with flour.
Knead about 7 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn once to bring greased side up.
Cover and let rise about 1 1/2 hours.
Knead down and shape into 2 loaves.
Cover and let rise about 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes. Butter top of loaves when done.

title: boeut georgian court
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Butterfly beef to 1-inch from bottom. Slice cooked lobster lengthwise and place inside sliced beef. Place asparagus lengthwise beside lobster meat.

title: mary's spice cake
directions: Boil for 5 minutes (rapid boil).
Cool at least 2 hours, then add 3 cups flour and 2 teaspoons baking soda.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan (buttered).
Serves 12.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bone.
Bring 2 cups broth to a boil with onion.
Remove from heat; add rice and let set, covered, for 5 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 325° until bacon is done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the first 6 ingredients using an electric mixer.

Mix flour, salt and baking soda together and mix into creamed ingredients. Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Crisscross with fork tines. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls flat into jellyroll pan.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed, onion salt, garlic powder, dip and sour cream.
Spread mixture onto crescent roll crust.
Top with chopped vegetables and shredded cheese.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: mom's cobbler
directions: Boil sugar and water, then set aside.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan in oven, then set aside.
Mix flour, shortening and milk into dough.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick rectangle.
Fill with fruit and roll up like a jelly roll.
Slice in 1/2-inch sections.
Place in baking pan and pour sugar water over it.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: u.m.w.'s cranberry salad for "360"
directions: Dissolve gelatin in first amount of cold water.
Dissolve cherry jello and sugar in hot water.
Add gelatin and stir until all ingredients are thoroughly dissolved.
Coarsely grind cranberries and oranges.
Finely chop apples and celery. Thoroughly mix all ingredients except lettuce and refrigerate in rectangular pans overnight.
Cut into serving squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Note: Save all juices!

title: oreo crunch pudding
directions: Set ice cream out to soften, then crumble cookies and put in bowl.
Melt butter and pour over crumbs and mix, then put 3/4 of the crumbs in 9 x 13-inch plastic freezer container.
Spoon ice cream over crumbs.
Spread Cool Whip on ice cream, then top with remaining crumbs.
Crush M&M's and put on top of crumbs and rush to freezer.
Freeze overnight or for 6 hours.

title: hamburger casserole(full meal)
directions: Put potatoes on to boil.
Mash with milk and butter.
Fry ground beef; drain juice.
Add onion, spices and tomato sauce. Let simmer on low heat.
Place hamburger sauce in a long pan. Place the corn on top. Spread the potatoes over this evenly. Place the cheese on top. Simmer in oven for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: diabetic fruit bars
directions: Boil together dates, prunes, raisins and water.
Add oleo. Mix together eggs, soda, salt, flour, vanilla and nuts.
