Add batter to fruit mixture. Bake in 9 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water; add 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Add shortening, rest of sugar and salt to hot milk.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Cool, then add egg.
Stir in softened yeast.
Stir flour into liquid mixture until well mixed.

title: polish cheese cake
directions: Melt butter; blend in sugar and remaining ingredients.
Press into shape in an 8-inch square Pyrex dish that had been well greased.
Refrigerate half hour or longer.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix pumpkin, oil, eggs, zucchini and 1/4 cup water.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Do not mix too thoroughly.
Pour into 1 or 2 greased 1-pound coffee cans half full.
Bake until straw comes out clean. Cool on rack.
Garnish with cream cheese or Cool Whip.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Heat milk and bread in a saucepan until bread is dissolved. Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Put salmon in a bowl.
Sprinkle lemon juice over salmon.
Add beaten eggs to milk mixture.
Add onions and celery.
Pour over salmon and mix thoroughly.
Put in flat pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt, cornstarch (or flour), and milk in a saucepan.
Heat over low flame, stirring constantly, until thick. In deep dish, place a layer of vanilla wafers, then a layer of sliced bananas, then a layer of pudding mix.
Continue this order, ending with the pudding mix.
Sprinkle some broken wafers on top.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Measure flour into pie plate; add salt.
Stir with fork. Combine milk and oil, do not stir; pour into flour and salt mixture.
Stir with a fork.
Form into ball.
Divide into two pastries.
Roll between wax paper.
Bake at 400° about 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes two 9-inch pie shells or one 2-crust pie.
Pie shells freeze very well.

title: country lemon loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs in casserole dish; add sugar and flour (blended together), pineapple, salt and 3 slices of bread.
Mix well.
Top with remaining slices of bread and pour melted butter over it. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring 6 cups water and 4 cups sugar to a boil (cool).
Blend 6 bananas and add to water sugar mixture.
Add orange juice and pineapple juice.
Add juice of 2 lemons.
Mix well.
Pour in 6 (1-quart) containers and freeze.
When ready to use, partially thaw and add 1 (2 liter) bottle of ginger ale, chilled, to each quart of frozen juice (prepared base).
This freezes well for a long time.

title: guru goodies
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter on low heat or in double boiler.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all.
Add Catalina dressing and tortilla chips.

title: orzo(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute onions and peppers in half of the margarine until soft; add mushrooms and cook a bit longer. Add this mixture to the cooked orzo to which the rest of the margarine has been added. Mix thoroughly. Add 1 can fried onions and mix. Pour into greased 2 1/2 or 3-quart (or 9 x 12) dish. Top with second can of French fried onions. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until crisp and browned. Enjoy.

title: mater-taters
directions: Melt butter and add oil to skillet.
Saute onion and add parsley.
Add tomatoes, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes over medium heat or until potatoes are done.

title: marzipan cupcake pastry shells
directions: Cream butter and sugar well in a mixing bowl with an electric mixer.
Add egg yolks and almond extract.
Mix well.
Blend in flour.
Chill
for 1 hour for easier handling.
Pinch off marble size pieces and press in bottom and sides of tiny ungreased muffin pan.
Bake at 375°
for 7 to 8 minutes.
Make filling and frosting.

title: whole wheat breadlubbock, texas
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 c. water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well then add whole wheat flour and then unbleached flour.
Knead then let raise 1 hour.
Knead again, let raise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until it sounds hollow.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: shrimp relish
directions: Mix parsley, oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper.
Combine cooked, clean shrimp and onion.
Refrigerate in dressing overnight, stirring occasionally.
Serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Put the pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put dry cake mix over pie filling.
Put melted butter, coconut and walnuts on top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sonny's chili
directions: Saute onions in water.
Add ground meat.
When meat is half cooked, add chili seasoning and salt, pepper, garlic and hot sauce, if desired.

title: angel whip salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients; chill.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: five minute soup
directions: In a soup pot, heat the chicken broth.
Add the vegetables and leftover meat.
Bring to boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Season with black pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Soften gelatin in cold water and dissolve in hot jello.
Stir strawberries into hot liquid.
Add cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Pour into oblong pan and chill until set.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Sift flour with all spices and salt.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture alternately with beaten eggs; beat well after each addition. Sprinkle a small amount of flour over fruits or nuts; add jam and fold in batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(This was Harvey Brooks favorite cake made by his cook.
Over 100 years old.)

title: banana bread
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add bananas, nuts and flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: butterscotch spice nut cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed.
Add margarine.
Pour into cake mix. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan (9 x 13-inch). Drop butterscotch chips over cake.
Sprinkle pecans over chips. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, food coloring and vinegar.
Bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: orange delighteverton, missouri
directions: Drain oranges and pineapples and stir in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix in dry Jello and it is ready to serve.

title: "best ever meat loaf"
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Put in pan and bake 1 hour.
Remove from oven and slather top with ketchup.
Return to oven and bake 40 minutes more.
Enjoy.

title: broccoli and macaroni salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: quick and simple shepherd's pie
directions: Cook hamburger, then run under hot water in colander for 30 seconds; set aside.
Prepare potatoes following directions for 6 helpings, then set aside.
In large cast-iron skillet, dump hamburger meat, chopped onion, corn and vegetable soup.
Top with mashed potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: Scald milk with chocolate added to it.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir milk gradually into dry ingredients.
Cook over boiling water for 10 minutes.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens.

title: lemon raspberry ribbon pie
directions: In a small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until thickened and clear.
Cool 10 minutes.
Chill thoroughly about 20 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine milk, lemon juice and food coloring, if desired.
Fold in whipped cream. Spread 1/3 lemon mixture into pie shell. Top with raspberry mixture, then remaining lemon mixture. Chill thoroughly. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into 4 portions. Combine flour and salt. Pound into meat.
Set aside remaining flour. Brown meat in a small amount of hot oil (2 tablespoons).
Place meat in a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in deep baking dish and add diced ham as desired. To make sauce in saucepan, mix the remaining ingredients and stir until thickens.
Pour over potatoes and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: chocolate peanut butter muffins
directions: Blend milk, cereal, brown sugar, peanut butter, oil and eggs. Add flour, baking powder, salt and chocolate chips, stirring and mixing well. Fill pans 3/4 full and bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes. Makes 6 muffins.

title: cherry tomato salad
directions: Mix everything together and chill.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients the day before serving in a large bowl and marinate.
Serve chilled.

title: raisin energy bars
directions: Simmer the first 5 ingredients in a sauce pan till thick (they won't get really thick).
Take off heat, add vanilla and cool.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Italian flavoring.
Spread on rye bread with a slice of cucumber.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Combine cornstarch, salt and sugar with 1 cup milk.
Scald remaining milk and add to cornstarch mixture.
Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla. Cool.
Alternate layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding in large, shallow dish.
Chill.
May be topped with whipped cream.

title: vanilla sugar
directions: Blend sugar and vanilla extract in a bowl. Spread it on a tray lined with wax paper and let dry for about 4 hours.
Press out any lumps with a wooden spoon and store in an airtight container.

title: blueberry betty
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash and drain berries in a colander. Place them in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with the lemon juice and cinnamon.
Sift flour and sugar together.
With a knife or pastry blender chop in the butter until it is crumbly. Sprinkle the mixture over the berries and bake for 45 minutes. Serve with the ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: mrs. foreman's rolls
directions: Dissolve warm water and yeast.
Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add boiling water, salt, cold water and eggs; beat after each ingredient.
Stir in yeast.
Add flour, 2 cups at a time.
Put in large bowl.
Cover with Saran Wrap; let rise about 2 hours.
Punch down and refrigerate.
Roll out 2 hours before time to bake.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Add raisins to boiling water. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add baking soda.
Let cool awhile.
Cream remaining ingredients. Combine with raisin mixture. Pour in 3 well-greased cans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until done.

title: cassava bibingka(snack)
directions: Pour all ingredients in a big mixing bowl.
Make sure everything is thoroughly mixed (no lumps).
Pour in a baking dish. Bake at 375°.
Check while baking, like what you would do when baking a cake.
When almost done, pour the condensed milk on top, making sure that it is evenly distributed.
Bake at 400° top 450° until it's caramelized.
Serve warm or cold.

title: stromboli
directions: Let bread rise.
Pat out dough on 2 greased cookie sheets. Spread mustard lightly.
Layer ham, American cheese, salami, Provolone cheese, pepperoni, sausage (sliced in bite-size pieces) and Mozzarella cheese.
Also, you can add any of the optional items between meat and cheese.
Roll up side of dough over meat and cheese to close.
Use just enough water to seal ends (toothpicks may have to be used to hold dough together).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with side of spaghetti sauce.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: the "now famous" cheese ring
directions: Combine all ingredients (except preserves).
Mix well.
Chill. Mold into a ring.
Fill center of ring with preserves.
Serve with crackers.

title: nutty corn flakes crunch
directions: Heat margarine in 3-quart saucepan until melted.
Stir in brown sugar until blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cereal and nuts are coated. Spread in thin layer on ungreased cookie sheet; cool.
Break into pieces.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix together soup and sour cream. Add all other ingredients. Spray casserole dish with Pam and add mixture. Spread crushed Ritz crackers on top, then pour melted butter over top of crackers. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no sugar cucumber pickles
directions: Mix vegetables and salt; let stand 3 hours in crushed ice. Drain.
Put in large vessel.
Pour in vinegar, sweetener and spices.
Heat to boiling point; do not boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Rub Bundt pan with Crisco. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar. Mix oil and sugar together. Add cream. Add cake mix, eggs and poppy seed.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Put flour and sugar in bowl. Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Mix with fork. Pour in greased oblong pan and bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Whip all ingredients together.
Dip fresh fruit (apples, grapes, strawberries, peaches, bananas, melons, etc.).

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in apples.
Add vanilla.
Bake
in greased 10-inch tube pan for 45 minutes at 325°.
Yields 1 (10-inch) tube pan.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into hot, greased skillet. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fat free dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients; spread evenly in shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the crumbs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine egg whites, sugar, berries and lemon juice in large bowl.
With electric beater, beat at high speed to stiff peaks, about 10 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon over crumbs; top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight.
Will cut 12 to 15 squares.
(Trim with whole strawberries, optional.)

title: stuffed eggplant rolls
directions: Wash eggplant, remove stems, peel and slice.
Dredge eggplant in flour, dip in beaten eggs and fry until golden brown.
Pat dry.

title: confetti rice
directions: Slightly cook carrots and celery; drain and set aside.
In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towels. Drain all but 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Add rice, carrots, celery and peas.
Cook until heated through, about 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in bacon.
Serve with soy sauce, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and 1 pint strawberries in saucepan. Cook over direct heat 8 to 10 minutes, stirring until sauce is thick, smooth and clear.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice. Let mixture cool.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over bottom of baked pie shell.
Fill with 1 pint of whole berries and pour cooled mixture over the berries.
Cool and top with whipped cream when ready to serve.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, oleo, shortening and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.

title: cranberry christmas salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a measuring cup, reserve pineapple. Add water to juice to make 1 cup liquid.
Bring to a boil and add jello.
Add cold water.
Chill 30 minutes.
In a bowl combine drained pineapple and cranberry sauce.
When well blended, put in a 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm and spread with Creamy Cheese Frosting.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: campbelled eggs
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook green pepper and onion in drippings until tender. In bowl, stir soup until smooth.
Gradually blend in eggs and pepper.
Pour in skillet.
Cook over low heat.
Lift cooked portions until eggs are completely set.
Garnish with bacon.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Mix meat and cracker crumbs which have been soaked in milk. Mix other ingredients together.
Pour 1 cup of this mixture over meat and crackers.
Make into small balls.
Place into baking dish.
Pour rest of liquid over meat.
Cook in oven at 400° for 40 or 50 minutes.

title: strawberry tapioca salad
directions: Combine pudding and strawberry jello.
Add water.
Cook on stove until thick.
Let cool.
Add strawberries and bananas.
Add Cool Whip.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown
meat
and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and mix well, then
cool.
In
a	large salad bowl toss together bell pepper, onion,
tomatoes,
lettuce,
cheese and kidney beans. Chill
until ready
to	serve.	Just
before
serving stir in seasoned	ground beef, salad dressing, corn chips and seasonings.

title: cheesy sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fry sausage; drain and cool.
Coat cheese and sausage with dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour sausage mixture into pie crust.
Add veggies, then pour egg mixture over all.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until browned and filling is set.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes, then slice and serve. Serves 6.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown bacon and cook onion and celery with garlic and basil until tender.
Sir in soups, water, tomatoes, ditali and salt.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar in a large bowl over hot water until melted.
Cool 10 minutes.
Beat eggs into mixture one at a time. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture with chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into greased 10 x 15-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: glazed carrots(serves 5 or 6)
directions: Wash carrots and quarter lengthwise.
Cook about 20 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Keep hot.

title: buuelos(sweet fried bread)
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and sugar in a large mixing bowl and cut in margarine.
Add eggs and milk to flour mixture and work mixture into a dough.
Knead dough until it is smooth and elastic.
Form dough into balls the size of an egg.
Cover dough and set aside for 15 minutes.
Roll each ball of dough into a circle that is 4-inches in diameter.
Cut a small hole in center of each circle.
Place circles of dough between single layers of waxed paper until all are rolled and ready for deep-frying.
Heat 2-inches of shortening in a heavy pan at medium-high heat.
Fry buuelos with a Cinnamon-Sugar Coating or Glaze (recipes follow) before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in casserole bowl.

title: amaretto dip for fruit
directions: In mixer or blender cream ingredients together.
Not fruit. Arrange fruit around bowl of dip.

title: sand tarts
directions: Put cake flour and powdered sugar in bowl.
Add butter; mix with
electric
beater
until butter is cut up fine.
Add vanilla and
nuts.
Mix
with
large
spoon
until all sticks together. Then make little rolls or balls and place on cookie sheet.
Cook for 1 hour, then turn cookies over for 5 minutes. Bake in 275° oven until light brown.
Shake in bag of powdered sugar lightly.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Lay hash browns on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread 1/4 cup butter and chopped onion over potatoes.
Combine soup, sour cream and cheese.
Spread over potatoes.
Crunch corn flakes and mix with 1/4 cup butter; spread over the top.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: debbie's chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie shell and set aside. Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together. Sift the mixture and set aside. In a medium size saucepan, mix, milk and egg yolks. Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until almost boiling. Then add the dry ingredient mixture slowly. Stir constantly until thick. Remove from heat. Use electric mixer to blend in vanilla. Blend until smooth. Pour into pie shell. Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: mom's special cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage finely.
Boil 3 eggs and chop.
Chop 1/2 onion and 1/2 carrot should be shredded.
Shred pepper also.
Mix all together in large bowl.
Add in oil and salad dressing; mix well. Decorate with additional shredded carrots and green pepper strips. Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla; add to dry ingredients, beating well.
Add zucchini; stir in nuts. Turn into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased loaf pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 55 minutes or until done.

title: dutch's scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown potatoes and onions.
Cook to tender,
add cheese to taste.
Add milk and cook another 10 to 15 minutes until all cooked together.

title: sponge cake
directions: Sift together flour, only 1 cup of the sugar and baking powder.
Separate the eggs.
Combine egg whites, salt and cream of tartar; beat until soft mounds form, then add 1/2 cup sugar, a tablespoon at a time.
Beat until very stiff.
Beat egg yolks; combine with water, vanilla and lemon extract.
Add dry ingredients to egg yolk mixture.
Fold in egg white mixture.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Cool; frost with Fluffy Icing.

title: cranberry cream punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl and let stand at room temperature for 10 to 15 minutes.
Chill remaining ingredients and pour over sherbet.

title: shakertown corn pudding
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in corn and milk.
Pour into buttered casserole. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, stirring once after the first 15 minutes.
Casserole is done when golden brown and a knife comes out clean.

title: french potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, gently toss with shallots, a sprinkling of salt and pepper, stock, vinegar and parsley.
Let steep for 10 minutes.
Toss gently several times.
Taste; correct seasoning and oil.
Toss before serving.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cukes in jars, add 1 or 2 heads of dill, cover with brine and seal.

title: eggplant skillet
directions: Cook beef, onion and celery until meat is brown.
Drain off extra fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, oregano and chili powder. Season eggplant slices with salt and pepper.
Arrange on top of meat sauce.
Cover and simmer until eggplant is tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with cheese (Cheddar).
Sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Mix 2 cups of flour, 2 sticks melted margarine, and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Press in bottom and on sides of 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in shallow dish. Dredge chicken breasts in mixture. Shake off excess.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Place chicken in water and cook until done (15 or 20 minutes). Drain and remove from bone.
Coarsely chop and set aside.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Coarsely chop apple; dip in pineapple juice to prevent browning.
Combine chicken, pineapple, apple, grapes, salad dressing and whipped topping.
Chill 2 hours and serve on lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry no-bake cheesecake
directions: Make a syrup out of the fructose, agar, orange liqueur and water, simmering for 20 minutes.
You may need to add a little water to maintain one cup total liquid.
Mix starch with 1/4 cup of water and add syrup 5 minutes before it is ready.
Stir until clear. Blend liquid with the soy cream cheese and tofu until smooth.
Add zest and vanilla while blending.
Fold in blueberries.
Spread mixture into crust.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: creamed cucumber pickles
directions: Going to school in a little Melonite Town, I ate some great meals.
Belle made this for me every time I went out to the cottage.

title: chicken ala rice
directions: Mix soups with the water or broth.
Cover the bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish with the rice.
Lay chicken pieces over rice. Cover with the mixture of soups and water or broth.
Dot with the chopped pimento.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: sparkling cranberry punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice and lemonade in punch bowl.
Add water immediately before serving.
Garnish with fresh lemon slices.
If desired, make an ice mold using a portion of the mineral water. Serves 25.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add bread cubes, milk and salt.
Add sausage and cheese last.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Let set a few minutes before cutting.
This recipe can be prepared the night before.
You can add more eggs and bread to serve more people.

title: lemon-orange sherbet(this is a tasty treat.)
directions: In a saucepan, cook sugar, syrup and water to a soft ball stage.
(Use your candy thermometer.)
In a bowl, beat egg whites with salt until stiff, but not dry.
Add heated sugar and syrup mixture and beat until mixtures form peaks.
Fold in fruit juice and place in freezing tray.
When frozen, cut and serve.
Serves 6.

title: what?  you want cobbler now!
directions: Put dry cake mix in cake pan; add fruit and juice on top. Swirl knife through cake mix, not too much!
Slice cube of margarine on top.
Stick in hot oven (375°) and bake until top is bubbly and brown.
Very rich, easy and hot.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine the egg, onion soup and cracker crumbs. Crumble beef over mixture and mix well.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in a greased 11 x 7 x 2 inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix walnuts and parsley; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients thoroughly; shape into ball.
Refrigerate until firm. Roll ball in nuts/flakes until coated.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Combine and blend until smooth the oil, eggs, cake mix and water.
Add sour cream and pudding mix.
Fold in chocolate chips. Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool slightly, then remove from pan.

title: asparagus
directions: Cook asparagus in salted water until tender, 5 to 10 minutes. Drain off water; place into dish.
Cook other ingredients until thick and smooth.
Pour over asparagus.
Enjoy!

title: marbled pecan pound cake
directions: Beat butter and 1/2 cup shortening at medium speed with electric mixer about 2 minutes or until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix at low speed just until blended after each addition. Stir in vanilla.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole in oven or microwave.
Measure and mix lightly sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted margarine, then pour fruit with juice over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown on top.
(To make it even easier, use self-rising flour and omit baking powder and salt.
If using peaches, add 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg to dry ingredients.)

title: bacalhau de molho fofo (portuguese)(codfish casserole)
directions: Soak codfish overnight in cold water to decrease the salt. Peel potatoes and cut in thick slices.
Boil in individual pots, fish, potatoes and 3 eggs.
When done, peel eggs; separate white and yolks and cut whites in thin rings.
Yolks, mash with a fork, adding salt and pepper to taste.
In deep casserole dish, place layers of fish, 1/2 codfish in bite size pieces, then 1/2 of sliced potatoes, 1/2 of finely cut parsley and 1/2 of black olives. Repeat, making 2 layers of each.
On top, display slices of hard-boiled white egg slices.
In 2-quart pot, pour 2 cups olive oil; heat to very hot.
Pour mashed egg yolks in.
It will come up boiling and forming very fast.
Have casserole dish ready next to the stove.
Pour olive oil mixture over layers immediately.
It is ready to eat.
It is good as a leftover.
You may want to add a little olive oil before warming up if it looks like it is needed.

title: vermicelli with lemony green vegetables
directions: Cook vermicelli as directed on package.
Drain.
While vermicelli is cooking, cook vegetables in butter in 10-inch skillet over medium heat about 7 minutes, stirring frequently until crisp-tender.
Toss with lemon peel.
Remove vegetables and keep warm.

title: dough art recipe
directions: You will need cookie cutters.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Crush Oreos into small crumbs.
Save 1/2 cup for top.
Mix the rest with melted butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut ice cream into slices and press on top of Oreos.
Heat hot fudge in microwave and pour over ice cream.
Add a layer of peanuts.
Cover and freeze.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip and remaining Oreo crumbs.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Sprinkle dry yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Pour boiling water over sugar, Crisco and salt.
Blend and cool.
Add beaten eggs, then flour (about 6 cups).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican tortilla casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and pour off fat.
Stir in soups; mix well, then add taco seasoning and mix again.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, put about 1/2 meat mixture and top with tortillas folded in half.
Cover with Monterey Jack cheese.
Add remaining meat mixture.
Add more tortillas and top with Cheddar cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and dish is hot.

title: broccoli bake(serves 6)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in broccoli and 1/2 can of the onions.

title: orange pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into container of ice cream freezer.
Freeze as usual when making ice cream in an electric or hand cranked freezer.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling over bottom of pan. Spread dry cake mix over and pour melted butter on.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Can be served with Cool Whip or ice cream.
Delicious and easy!

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
This is great served with sliced green apples.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put everything in a crock-pot and after butter has melted, add cooked meat and simmer.

title: crab cheese quarters
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients together.
Drain crab meat and fold into spread.
Spread over muffins.
Freeze on cookie sheet. Cut into quarters and store in plastic bag until ready to use.

title: potato cheese chowder
directions: Place all ingredients except processed cheese spread in 2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave covered on High 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in Cheez Whiz until melted.
Microwave uncovered on High, stirring every 2 to 3 minutes until desired consistency.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie(low-fat)
directions: Beat Egg Beaters and 1/2 cup sugar until thick.
Add pumpkin, milk, salt and spices; cook slowly until thick.
Add gelatin softened in cold water.
Stir until gelatin dissolves. Add egg whites, beaten with remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour into cooled, baked shell and chill.
If desired, top with whipped cream.

title: orange blossom balls
directions: Thaw orange juice to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together, except coconut.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Refrigerate until served.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix together the peanut butter and sugar with hands.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and chocolate chips; spread over mixture.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered at 350 degrees.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust. Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
(Mixture will be thick.) Stir in pumpkin and spices until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with additional whipped topping, if desired.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Line bottom of casserole dish with Tater Tots.
Spread uncooked ground beef evenly over Tater Tots.
Add chopped onion in layer.
Layer cream of mushroom soup, add beef bouillon, salt and pepper.
Layer leftover Tater Tots on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit, marshmallows and powdered sugar; blend well. Thin cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Mix with fruit.
Fold in whipped cream, nuts and vanilla.
Freeze just until mixture is firm.
Unmold and serve with additional salad dressing or whipped cream.
Garnish with pineapple wedges and cherries.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 14 carat cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Add sugar, salad oil and eggs. Mix well. Add carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut. Blend thoroughly. Pour into 3 (9-inch) round greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven and cool in pans for 10 minutes. Turn out and cool thoroughly. Fill and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pineapple spinach salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 1/2 cup juice for dressing.
Mix pineapple with bacon, spinach (torn in pieces), raisins, celery and onion.
Combine reserved pineapple juice with garlic, vinegar, oil and sugar.
Add to salad and toss.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: soft-as-a-cloud sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine sour cream and half and half; add to flour mixture, stirring with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thick and cut with a floured 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pork roast with beer
directions: Brown pork roast on top of stove with oil in Dutch oven on all sides until well browned.
Remove from pan.
Brown onions and garlic until done.
Place roast back in pan.
Add beer and mustard.
Stir.
Place in oven and cook until done at 350°, approximately 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Baste roast occasionally.
Add 1 glass of water to roast when 1/2 cooked.
Remove roast when done. Thicken gravy with cornstarch and water.
Goes well with mashed potatoes.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
In a large bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture on top of the cake batter and marble with a spatula.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes, until done.
Cool in pan and sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: cheesy stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Mix cheese, parsley and bread crumbs with melted margarine; set aside.
Put 1/4 cup of cheese mixture in middle of breast; fold in half.
Cover with 1/4 cup mixture (under skin).
Sprinkle with paprika (on top of skin).

title: sweet potato roll
directions: Mix together these ingredients.
Grease bottom of jelly roll pan (10 x 15 x 2-inch) and line with waxed paper.
Pour mixture on wax paper.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
When done, roll up with paper while hot and refrigerate until cool.

title: eileen's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix together well.
Turn into large pan and shape into a loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: black walnut candy
directions: Boil sugar, milk, soda and butter until it foams a soft-ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add black walnuts and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Pour into butter pan or dish and cool before cutting in squares.

title: mellow melon cooler
directions: Wrap ice cubes in clean towel and crush with a rolling pin or hammer.
Place cantaloupe, milk, sugar and crushed ice in blender container.
Process on low until ice begins to blend into mixture. Increase speed to high and process until smooth.
Garnish, if desired, and serve immediately.
Makes 3 cups.
One cup serving equals 90 calories; 1 gram fat, 3 mg. cholesterol and 1 1/3 servings of fruit.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and stir well.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Crush 2 cups corn flakes.
Stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over mixture and bake 50 minutes.

title: tang clouds
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Press 3/4 of dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together in a saucepan the pineapple, Tang, sugar, cornstarch and nuts.
Cook until thick.
Pour filling over dough, spreading evenly.
Drop remaining dough in spots over filling.
Bake at 350° for 27 minutes.

title: oven-browned cornsticks
directions: Melt margarine in jelly roll pan or cookie sheet in 400° oven. Mix together baking mix and corn.
Pat out onto waxed paper dusted with baking mix to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into squares about 2-inches wide.
Dip both sides into melted margarine and place in baking pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Easy, but delicious!

title: cheese grits
directions: Add all ingredients; mix well and pour into a well-greased casserole. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake 15 minutes more.

title: smokehouse spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add other ingredients, except spaghetti.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add spaghetti; mix and pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach blueberry fruit pie
directions: In large bowl, combine peaches, blueberries, sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix lightly.
Spoon into pie crust-lined 9-inch pan.
Dot with margarine.
Top with second crust.
Flute edges and slash design in top crust.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with vanilla ice cream if desired.
Frozen peaches and blueberries can be substituted for fresh.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drop by tablespoons onto a cookie sheet.

title: spiced beef roast
directions: Crush fennel seed, mustard seed and whole black peppercorns. Set aside.
Trim fat from roast.
Place roast on rack in a shallow roasting pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in half of dry ingredients into sugar mixture and blend well.
Stir in remaining dry ingredients alternately with eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots; mix well.
Add pecans and mix well.
Add pineapple and coconut. Pour into lightly oiled pans.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sugar.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat 10 minutes.
Bake in prepared tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Place vegetables in saucepan.
Add onion, flour, herbs and pepper; stir well.
Add chicken broth and milk; heat until boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Just before serving, stir in the grated cheese and cream cheese.
Add mustard.
Serve immediately.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach in microwave for 7 minutes per box.
Then press out water.
Combine in casserole dish the spinach, eggs, mayo, Tabasco sauce, soup, lemon juice and cheese.
Mix well. Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Drizzle melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Put apples in a large pot; set aside.
Bring to a boil all the other ingredients, then pour over apples.
Cook for 30 minutes, then place in jars and seal.

title: cherry tart
directions: Mix by hand all dry ingredients.
Add egg and cherries.
Add oleo and nuts.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Add eggs to milk; mix well.
Cut steak into serving pieces, dip steak into egg mixture, dip into crumbs, brown steak on both sides in hot fat.
Season with pepper and salt.
Cover, steam over low heat for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a ball.
Roll in chili powder, if desired.

title: great hollow fish chowder
directions: Saute onions and leeks in butter until soft.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper and water or fish stock; bring to a boil.
Layer on top of vegetables.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add light cream and warm, but do not allow to boil. Correct seasonings to taste.

title: black-eyed peas vinaigrette
directions: Soak peas overnight in water; drain.
Place the garlic, thyme, bay leaf and 4 sprigs fresh parsley in a cheesecloth bag.
Place the peas and the bag in a saucepan with 8 cups of water.
Add 1 onion studded with 2 whole cloves.
Cook for 1 1/4 hours.
Discard the cheesecloth bag and the onion.

title: egg rolls
directions: Heat wok or large skillet.
Pour oil around the sides.
Add the chicken, onions, cabbage, water chestnuts and celery. Stir-fry until vegetables are crisp-tender in texture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put 2 tablespoons of mixture in the center of egg roll wrapper.
Fold sides in.
Roll up.
Moisten edges to seal with a mixture of 1/2 cup milk and 1 tablespoon cornstarch. Fry in oil until golden brown.
Serve with hot mustard, plum sauce or sweet-sour sauce.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: whole wheat coffee rolls
directions: Put
the
flour
in the oven and warm 20 minutes.
Dissolve the
yeast	in the lukewarm water.	Mix the oil, honey, salt
and hot
water.
Let it cool.
Add 1 egg to the mixture and
the dissolved
yeast.
Stir
in the warm flour.
Put the dough into the refrigerator and let it cool 1 hour.

title: fish soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water, undrained tomatoes, mixed vegetables, celery, onion, bouillon granules, oregano, garlic and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in fish. Return just to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: great chicken
directions: Place washed chicken in a flat glass or metal container with sides.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 1 package Lipton soup, preserves and Russian dressing over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, basting often.
Cover with foil if browning too fast!

title: corn salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Roll in little balls.
Flatten with a milk glass and bake in 375° oven 15 minutes or until done (on cookie sheet).
Do not grease the pan. When cookies start to brown around edges they should be done.

title: chicken cutlets with artichokes, tomato and mozzarella(serves 2)
directions: Sprinkle chicken cutlets with salt and pepper and dredge in flour, shaking off excess.
In a heavy skillet, heat 1 tablespoon butter and the oil over moderately high heat until foam subsides and saute the cutlets until they are just cooked through, transferring to a heated platter.
Remove skillet from heat.
Add the garlic; cook over moderately low heat.
Add the wine and lemon juice and simmer until reduced by half.
Remove from heat; add remaining 1 tablespoon butter and swirl until incorporated.
Pour sauce over cutlets and top cutlets with tomato, artichoke hearts and Mozzarella.
Broil about 3 inches from heat until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Sift together the flour, spices and salt.
To half of this mixture, add the gumdrops, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Cream shortening and add sugar gradually, creaming well.
Add eggs one at a time to cream mixture, beating well.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add the remaining half of dry mixture alternately with applesauce and soda, stirring well.
Stir in floured gumdrops, raisins and nuts, blending thoroughly.
Pour in 2 greased waxed paper lined loaf pans (9 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch).
Bake in a slow oven at 300° for about 2 hours.

title: kluski(polish dumplings)
directions: Use a deep kettle 2/3 full of water.
Bring to boil.
Peel potato and grate finely.
Add salt.
Start adding flour a little at a time, to grated potato until it is hard to mix with a spoon and very stiff.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon-size balls into boiling water, a few at a time.
Be careful so it does not boil over.
Dumplings will rise to top when just about done.
Remove from water and drain. Use with Czarnina.
May also be used with pork chops, beef or fried with onions.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, putting half the seasoned crumbs in the mixture.
Put in buttered shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Cook at 350°
until hot and bubbling, about 30 minutes.

title: summer sausage(trail blazer)
directions: Mix well and divide into 3 parts.
Put each on foil and shape into rolls.
Put on cookie sheet and chill for 24 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Pierce foil before cooking.

title: ham bake
directions: Saute onion in butter; add soup, 1/2 the cheese and garlic. Then add mushrooms, broccoli, rice and ham and stir in pimentos. Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (covered).
Ten minutes before done, uncover and put on remaining cheese and fried onion rings.

title: glorified brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add sifted flour, cocoa, salt and nuts.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until done in greased and floured 9-inch square pan at 325°.
Cover with marshmallows; return to oven only long enough to cause marshmallows to stick together.
Cool; top with favorite chocolate icing.
Serve in squares.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Place cottage cheese in food processor or blender and blend until smooth.
Add next 5 ingredients and process until well mixed.
Place mixture in bowl; cover and chill until ready to serve.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine cooked chicken with remaining ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mushroom zucchini pie
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and zucchini until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Drain and add flour, salt, pepper and thyme.
Mix to coat.
Remove from heat.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients with milk, egg and oil and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bake in a well greased iron skillet at 350° until golden brown.
Serve hot with ham hocks and greens and a glass of ice tea on the side.
Scrumptious!!

title: banana cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Do not overbake.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in well greased or Pam sprayed loaf pan.

title: hazelnut torte
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Butter 10-inch spring-form pan and dust lightly with bread crumbs.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well with fork.
Save 1 1/2 cups of this mixture for topping.
Pat remaining mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Remove from oven and set aside to cool. Beat together cheese (room temperature), sugar, eggs, lemon juice, vanilla and milk.
When these are all mixed well, pour over cooled crust.
Sprinkle remaining topping over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and then refrigerate before cutting into squares because, if warm, they will crumble.

title: divinity
directions: Mix
sugar, syrup and water;
cook until mixture reaches 240° on
candy
thermometer.
Pour
1/2 of the mixture over the beaten egg
whites,
and
stir well.
Cook the remaining 1/2 of the sugar mixture
until it reaches 290° on candy thermometer. Pour into egg white mixture.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
This mixture hardens rapidly so it has to be finished quickly.

title: bess' baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bean pot and bake at 350° until bubbling hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy beef wellington
directions: Thaw patty shells.
Brown meat on both sides.
Set aside. Melt butter in skillet.
Add wine.
Saute onion and mushrooms until tender.
Roll out patty shells.
Place piece of tenderloin on pastry; top with onion and mushrooms.
Wrap pastry around meat. Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tony's favorite toasted seasoned pecans
directions: Pour 1/2 pecans in microwavable bowl.
Dot 3 Tbsp. butter and 1 Tbsp. of season salt over 1/2 the pecans.
Pour other 1/2 pecans over the above.
Dot with 3 Tbsp. butter and 1 Tbsp. season salt (or to taste).
Microwave uncovered 6 to 7 minutes stirring every 2 minutes let cool and enjoy.

title: grandmother haggard's boiled custard
directions: Warm milk in double boiler.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Pour into warm milk in thin stream.
Stir until custard thickens (forever!) and coats spoon.
Remove from heat.
Continue stirring until cool. Add a generous amount of cognac (Grandmother used a good bourbon) before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Grease 8 X 8 X 2 square pan. Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm.
Good with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Cube cheese and mix all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low until cooked through.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.
If you like it hot and spicy, add salsa.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Add eggs, butter or margarine, buttermilk, vanilla and 2/3 can coconut; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining coconut over top of pie. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: munchies
directions: Combine butter, molasses and sugar to make syrup.
Stir and bring to a boil. Cover and cook approximately 3 minutes. Remove cover and cook but don't stir to the almost hard crack stage. Pour syrup over cooked popcorn and stir well.
Add nuts of choice.
Toss lightly. Cool and place in tight seal tins.

title: bacon potato chowder
directions: In saucepan cook bacon pieces over medium heat until browned. Add onions, continue cooking until tender (2 to 3 minutes) and drain.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper and cook until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to low, stir in soup, sour cream and milk.
Continue cooking, stir occasionally until heated, 3 to 5 minutes.
Yields 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: quiche
directions: Mix eggs, sour cream, broccoli, onion rings, cheese and ham in bowl and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Wonderful if served with sliced tomatoes.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Pour melted margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add sliced and drained peaches.
Mix peach juice, egg, milk, flour, pudding mix and 1/2 cup sugar together and pour over top of sliced peaches.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Pour into big heating pan that can go onto the stove.
Heat, but don't let it come to a boil.
It's ready to serve.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda and cocoa twice to mix
thoroughly.
Add
mayonnaise,
cold
water	and vanilla. Mix and bake in
a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: tuna temper
directions: Arrange in layers and cover with cream sauce.
Top with crackers crumbs, dotted with butter.
Bake 1/2 hour in a 350° oven. Serves 6.

title: water chestnut-shrimp appetizers
directions: Wrap 1 shrimp and water chestnut slice with half slice bacon, secure with toothpick.
Combine butter, garlic, parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper in bowl and mix well.
Add shrimp rolls. Marinate for 1 hour or longer.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
At the same time in top of a double boiler over hot water melt caramels, margarine and evaporated milk.
Pour 1/2 prepared cake mix into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Pour caramel mixture over baked cake; sprinkle with chocolate pieces and pecans.
Pour remaining cake batter over all and bake for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: texas taco dip
directions: Spread jalapeno bean dip in 3-quart oblong glass dish.
Mash avocados and season with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Spread over jalapeno dip.

Combine sour cream with mayonnaise and taco seasoning and spread over avocado layer, then add on the following over chopped green onions seeded and pulp, chopped tomatoes, chopped olives and shredded cheese.
Dip can be divided in 2 (1 1/2-quart) oblong glass dishes.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and oil and beat well.
Stir in carrots, raisins, coconut and walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 1/4 x 5 1/4-inch loaf pan, or 2 small loaves. Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip(microwave)
directions: Place the package of broccoli on a paper plate. Cook on High for 6 minutes. Drain.
Place cheese in medium bowl.
Soften by heating on Medium-high for 2 minutes. Add soup and broccoli. Cook on Medium-high for 6 to 8 minutes or until bubbly around the edges.
Serve hot with crackers or raw veggies.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add other ingredients.
Mix these and pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until set.

title: wacky cake
directions: Add all ingredients in bowl and mix together until well mixed. You may use an electric mixer.
Grease and flour square cake pan (snack cake size).
Bake about 30 minutes, until toothpick is clean at 325°.

title: fall cranberry muffins
directions: Combine oil, eggs, milk and cranberries in mixer bowl; mix well.
Add flours, baking powder, baking soda, sugar, cinnamon and walnuts; mix just until moistened.
Fill paper-lined muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Combine well drained fruits; add marshmallows and coconut.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and carefully stir until all ingredients are mixed well.
Fold in about 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping and a dash of curry powder.

title: beef-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni but do not rinse.
To this mixture, add tomatoes, butter and spices.
Brown ground beef and onion until onion is clear.
Drain.
Add beef and onion to macaroni mixture.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cheese.
Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger barbecue(sloppy joes)
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Brown hamburger meat.
Mix onions, green pepper and celery.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes. Blend in tomato sauce, chili sauce, Worcestershire, pepper, salt, sugar and vinegar.
Simmer for about 15 minutes, stirring often. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: rabbit delight
directions: Joint rabbit and brown in oil.
Add broth and other ingredients. Cover and cook slowly until tender.

title: banana cake
directions: Note:
Have shortening at room temperature.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
(Do not line with paper.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: Add soda to flour.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, a third at a time.
Add bananas, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Turn into tube or loaf pan.
Put in slow oven for about one hour.

title: pork chop and potatoes
directions: Fry pork chops in skillet until browned and middle is done. Dice potatoes and fry in skillet until browned in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Mix potatoes with milk, soup and pepper.
Put potato mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan, then top with pork chops and place another layer of potato mixture on top of the pork chops.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: crispy zucchini or eggplant
directions: In a small bowl, combine the first 3 ingredients (or can use 1/2 cup Hidden Valley Ranch dressing in place of the 3 ingredients).
On a waxed paper, combine next 3 ingredients.
Brush both sides of the sliced zucchini with the mayonnaise mixture and coat using crumb mixture.
Place in shallow pan or baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes or until browned.

title: mock eggs benedict
directions: Our Georgia daughter, who is the oldest girl, gave me this recipe.
Jill is more interested in a career than cooking or housework.
Even so, she has given me several very good recipes and she is a good cook.

title: creamy pimento cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May have to add mayonnaise to make creamier.

title: scallop potato casserole
directions: Put ground beef in skillet.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper and season to taste with Creole seasoning.
Cook until done and beef is crumbly.
Drain all fat away.
Pour over bottom of casserole dish (oblong); sprinkle grated cheese over meat mixture covering all.
Place sliced potato wheels on entire top of casserole.
Mix cream of mushroom with milk and spoon over casserole.
Sprinkle lightly with Creole seasoning.
Garnish with paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Serve hot from oven with buttered rolls and green salad.

title: caramel apples(appetizers)
directions: Wash apples.
Cut apples into lightly salted water or add a couple drops of lemon juice to water to prevent discoloring. With mixer, whip cream cheese and ice cream topping together. Place mixture in dip bowls.
Drain apple pieces and insert toothpick into each.
Serve each guest with individual dip bowls, apples and toothpicks.
Dip away.

title: creole soup
directions: Combine
onions, peppers and tomatoes to the 1/2 gallon of water.
Cover
and
bring to a boil.
Break spaghetti into small pieces
and add to other ingredients.
Over a low fire, boil until
spaghetti
is
done, stirring frequently to avoid sticking. Serves 10 to 15.

title: hot fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add chocolate morsels and stir until melted.
Stir in nuts.
Pour over warm cake.
Spread quickly.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat together the lemon rind, eggs, buttermilk and margarine.
Stir in dry ingredients just until mixture is wet.
Stir in blueberries. Spoon in muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: "priestly pastry"(blueberry buckle coffee cake)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add 1 cup flour (sifted).
Add 1 cup sifted flour, salt, baking soda and eggs.
Place in 9-inch spring-form pan.
Add to the top the blueberries or any other fruit such as plums, sliced apples, sliced peaches or a combination of fruit.
Sprinkle top with sugar, lemon juice (flour if fruit is juicy) and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick chili
directions: Combine uncooked hamburger and veal/pork together.
Add onion, 1 cup of stewed tomatoes and 1 cup sauerkraut.
Add uncooked rice and mix by hand until rice is mixed in.
Remove core from cabbage and steam; leaves should fall off when cooked.
Place meat into cabbage leaves; do not overfill since rice will expand.
Continue filling and rolling until all meat is used.
As rolls are finished, layer in large roasting pan.
Cover cabbage rolls with unused cabbage leaves.
Pour the remainder of stewed tomatoes and sauerkraut over cabbage rolls.
Mix soup with 1 can of water and pour over all.
If tomato soup does not completely cover cabbage rolls, add another can of soup.
Cook at 350° for 2 hours or until rice is cooked.

title: crispy oven fried mexican chicken
directions: In large shallow pan (not aluminum) combine vegetable juice and hot sauce; add chicken parts and let marinate for 30 minutes at room temperature or cover and refrigerate for 3 hours; turn chicken frequently.
Drain chicken and discard marinade.
Spray a baking sheet with Pam cooking spray.
In a large plastic bag combine remaining ingredients.
Place chicken parts a few at a time in bag and shake to coat chicken; place pieces on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle any remaining crumb mixture over chicken and press to adhere.
Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and crisp.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order they are listed until smooth.
Pour into muffin cups (greased) or use cupcake holders. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: angel hair pasta with chicken
directions: Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in a skillet over medium heat;
add chicken. Cook, stirring, until chicken is cooked through, about 5 minutes. Remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.
Heat remaining oil in same skillet; add carrot to skillet; cook stirring for 4 minutes.
Add broccoli and garlic to skillet; cook stirring for 2 minutes longer.

title: haluski
directions: Cut the bacon into pieces; brown and drain.
Brown the onion with the bacon.
Then add the cabbage and let steam until tender. Mix the noodles and cabbage and serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan; spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling; spread evenly.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer; spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over cake mix.
Put butter on top.
Bake 48 to 53 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in warm oven for 20 minutes.
Let cool and store in covered container.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix both boxes of jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Add pineapple to mixture.
Mix mayonnaise and Eagle Brand milk, then add to jello mixture. Add nuts.
Congeal.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cookie dough may be sliced and placed on a lightly greased pizza pan, or it may be patted out on a pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: nantucket cranberry pie
directions: Wash and pick over cranberries.
Place on bottom of greased 10-inch pie pan (square or oblong pan may be used).
Sprinkel with 1/2 cup sugar and walnuts.
Mix together 1 cup sugar and melted margarine, then add flour, almond extract and beaten eggs. Mix well.
Pour batter over cranberries.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar in a 1 1/2-quart round baking dish.
Stir well until evenly blended.
Microwave on High for four minutes.
Stir in nuts and microwave on High three to five minutes until light brown.
Stir in butter and vanilla, blending well. Microwave on High one to two minutes.
Add soda and stir gently just until light and foamy.
Quickly pour onto lightly greased baking dish.
Cool.
Break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: holiday brew
directions: Combine all in slow cooker.
Heat on low for 3 hours.
Serve hot.

title: oven baked rice
directions: Combine rice, broth and vegetable oil in a 2-quart casserole. Pour water over rice; stir and cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Fluff before serving.
Garnish with fresh mint, if desired.

title: super snaps
directions: Cream together the brown sugar and shortening.
Add the egg and molasses.
Sift together and stir in the dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread all in one large greased cookie pan (jelly roll pan).
Sprinkle top with granulated sugar.
Bake only 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool slightly.
Cut straight rows the long way.
Cut diagonals the short way, making diamond shapes.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Blend melted butter and sugars together.
Stir in eggs (be sure butter has cooled), vanilla, oatmeal and cornflakes.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda, then add to other ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and chopped pecans.
Use an ice cream scoop to put cookie dough onto a large cookie sheet (about 6 to a sheet).
Bake at 350°
for about 18 minutes on top rack of oven.
Wonderful!

title: cinnamon roll cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, eggs and sour cream.
In a separate bowl, mix brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Mix with cake mix mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.
Punch holes in cake.
Glaze.

title: kidney bean casserole
directions: Saute onion and ground beef in margarine until browned.
Stir in salt, pepper and tomato paste.
Spoon half of mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with half of kidney beans, then half of cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: daffodil easter cake
directions: Beat until foamy the egg whites.
Add salt and cream of tartar. Beat until stiff but not dry.
Fold in carefully 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar.
Divide mixture.
Fold into one part 1/2 cup flour (sifted 5 times) and vanilla.
Fold into other part egg yolks (beaten), 2/3 cup flour (sifted 5 times) and orange extract.
Place by spoonfuls into ungreased 9-inch tube cake pan, alternating yellow and white batters as in marble cake.
Bake in 325° oven for 60 minutes.

title: cornish pastry
directions: Form pastry into ball.
Dust with flour and wrap in plastic. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: cajun beans
directions: Wash beans thoroughly and boil according to directions for 30 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and cook until tender.

title: nordic delights
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except coconut.
Beat at low speed until well mixed, 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in coconut. Divide dough in half.
Shape each ball into a 12 x 2-inch roll. Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours.

title: mom's scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in large Corning Ware type casserole.
Add flour and spices.
Stir and slowly add milk.
Heat over medium heat.
Add 1/4 pound cubed Velveeta.
Heat until thickened and hot, but not boiled.
Remove from heat when Velveeta/milk mix is smooth.
Add sliced potatoes, push down into sauce and mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Beat eggs, mayo, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add green pepper and onion.
Mix with zucchini.
Put in greased pan; dot with butter and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: best ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts and shred meat. Melt butter in large bowl. Break crackers up and pour into butter along with poppy seeds. This is your top and bottom crust. Spread 1/2 cracker mixture into bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix chicken, soups and sour cream and spread over crackers. Top with remaining cracker mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with fresh salad.

title: roast turkey
directions: Wash turkey and pat dry.
Stuff cavity with quartered carrot, celery, onion and orange.
Rub salt over skin and follow with melted butter.
Place turkey in brown grocery bag.
Put in shallow baking dish and close end, tucking under.
Bake at 325° for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and tear open bag to reveal beautiful golden brown turkey with moist meat.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Combine both packages of jello and water.
Blend this mixture into cream cheese.
Add pineapple, cream, lemon juice, horseradish and chopped nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: vegetable crunch
directions: Combine Veg-All, celery, onion and chestnuts.
Add cheese and mayonnaise, mixing well.
Place mixture in greased casserole; top with crushed crackers and dribble with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy cheese and veggie lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 11 x 7-inch baking pan with nonstick spray.
Spread 1/3 of the sauce on the bottom of the dish and arrange 3 noodles in a single layer over the sauce.
Top with another 1/3 of the sauce, all the Ricotta and veggies and 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheeses.
Then add the remaining 3 noodles in a single layer.
Spread evenly with remaining sauce, making sure to cover the noodles COMPLETELY.
Cover dish with foil and bake until noodles are tender and mixture is piping hot, about 1 hour. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Place apples in lightly buttered deep dish.
Sprinkle cake mix (dry) and cinnamon-sugar mixture over top.
Drizzle melted butter over top. Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: chicken
directions: Dust/shake one side of
chicken with first 4 ingredients.
Baste with barbecue sauce.
Repeat on other side. Grill and continue basting.
When cooked, place cheese on it to melt.
(Cheese looks triangular.)
Serve and enjoy.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Add peanuts, food coloring and cook until hard-ball stage or 250° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat; add butter and salt. Beat until mixture begins to sugar and thickens.
Turn out onto greased cookie sheet. Either slice into squares or break into pieces while still warm.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: In greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer 1/2 of potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over layers.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Meanwhile, in skillet brown pork chops on both sides.
Place chops on top of potatoes.
Cover and return to oven for 45 minutes or until chops are done.
Uncover during last 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries. Sprinkle with sugar and drain overnight. Add cut grapes and walnuts to cranberries. Fold in whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl combine butter, sugars and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Spread in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: quick simmer barbecue sauce
directions: Heat butter in a medium saucepan and lightly saute garlic, onions and mustard for about one to two minutes.
Add brown sugar, ketchup and vinegar.
Then add remaining and bring sauce to a boil, and simmer slowly for about 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook or bake chicken with celery and onion.
Remove skin and bones from chicken.
Bring broth and chicken to a boil.
Add lasagna noodles; cook until lasagna noodles are tender.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together well and add oats, chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by ice cream scoop on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Divide dough into 3 equal parts.
Shape into a ball about 1 1/2-inches around and 7-inches long.
Chill about 4 hours.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 8 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.
You can use this for peanut butter cookies also.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dad's dip
directions: Mix until creamy. Dip Fritos Scoops, Tostitos or veggies. You can also spread on flour tortillas and roll up.

title: basic recipe quick bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 320° for 1 hour in a loaf pan with only bottom greased.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into bottom of pizza pan.
Bake as directed.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with fruit such as strawberries, peaches, kiwi and blueberries.
Keep chilled.

title: mexican lettuce salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Fritos.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Add crushed Fritos just before serving.

title: sausage balls #1
directions: Mix dry ingredients and shortening with knives or pastry blender.
(This mixture can be stored in a covered container and used later.)
Add sausage and cheese to flour mixture; work up real well.
Mixture will be real stiff.
Roll into marble size balls.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes, or until they are golden brown.

title: ozark apple pudding
directions: Beat sugars and egg together.
Mix flour, baking powder and nutmeg together.
Add to sugar and egg mixture.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: chicken turnovers
directions: Cut cream cheese and margarine into flour.
Chill 1 hour. Roll out and cut in crescent shapes.
Place spoonful of chicken mixture (can chicken and cream of mushroom soup) into pastry and fold over.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
May be prepared ahead and frozen.
Bake a few minutes longer, if frozen.
The cream cheese mixture can be pressed into miniature muffin tins and filled with chicken mixture and baked.

title: golden chicken with garden vegetables
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Season chicken and brown pieces over moderately high heat, until golden on all sides, about 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and turn to glaze.
Drain excess fat. Pour Worcestershire sauce over all.
Cook for 15 minutes more, basting occasionally, until chicken and vegetables are tender. Stir in yogurt and cream and warm through.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Microwave butter and flour for 1 minute, then add milk and microwave 5 minutes.
Whisk mixture until thick (about like thick mashed potatoes).
Stir in cream cheese, cheese, cayenne pepper, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour about 2/3 of mixture into spinach and mix well.
Pour spinach mixture into greased casserole and spread remaining sauce on top of spinach.
Pour melted butter over crackers and mix well.
Top casserole with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly throughout.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir into mixture.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake until light brown at 375°
for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.
These cookies puff up, then flatten out.

title: party scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet; add onion and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk; stir constantly until thick.
Stir in cheese; blend well.
In 2-quart casserole, pour preceding mixture over potatoes and pimentos.
Mix bread crumbs, parsley, sesame seed and 4 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Good with Honeyed Ham or beef.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugars. Beat in egg, peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla. Stir in flour, oatmeal and water.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Pour 1 bag milk chocolate chips on top.
Let sit a minute.
Smooth with a spatula.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together well and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: fudgies(no bake)
directions: Combine butter, sugar, milk, cocoa and salt.
Bring to a boil. Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and nuts, then stir in oatmeal. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet or waxed paper (don't bake).
Will get hard when they get cold.

title: coconut sour cream dream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, making 2 (8-inch) layers.
Split both layers horizontally after they have cooled. Blend sugar, sour cream and coconut; chill.
Spread all, except 1 cup of the sour cream mixture, between the four layers.
Blend the remaining cup of the mixture with the whipped cream.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
Keep refrigerated after cutting.

title: wasps nest cake
directions: Cook pudding and milk until it starts to boil.
Add cake mix to pudding mixture and beat well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into 5 pieces each.
Mix all ingredients.
Add hot dogs.
Serve in chafing dish to keep mixture warm.
Guests are provided with toothpicks when hot dogs are served.

title: chicken avocado tortilla soup
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pan over medium heat, stir onion, garlic, cumin, oregano, chili powder and pepper until all spices are fragrant, approximately 1 minute. Add broth, diced tomatoes and green chilies. Cover and boil. Stack tortillas and cut in 1/8-inch wide strips. Add to pan. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: chicken strataserves 140 people!
directions: Remove 42 slices bread, butter it and cut into 1/2 inch cubes. Put aside for the top.
Slice the remaining bread into 1 inch cubes.
Divide bread cubes and cover bottoms of 2 large pans. Spread chicken over the cubes.
In a large bowl, whisk the eggs, add milk, salt and pepper and pour over the chicken.
In the same bowl combine mayonnaise, onions, and green pepper.
Spread into pans.
Spoon mushroom soup over the mixture.
Top with cubes. Cover and bake slowly in a medium oven for 2 hours.
This can be made the previous day, kept in the refrigerator and baked the same.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.

title: sunday chicken-rice bake
directions: Stir together soup, milk, onion soup mix and mushrooms; divide in half.
Put 1/2 of mixture in 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add chicken; mix second half mixture with 1 cup rice and 1 package peas and carrots.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: six cup fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill well.
Garnish with cherries, if desired.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: apple strudel
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Put apples in buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Make crumbs with flour, butter and brown sugar.
Mix until little balls form. Sprinkle crumbs over apples.
Pat down.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes; 400° for 30 minutes for glass pans.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook all in boiler slowly about 1 hour before using.
Store leftover sauce in refrigerator.
Keeps well.
Brush over Boston butt, sliced 1 inch thick, or chicken.
Cook slowly and brush with sauce after each turn.
