Takes a long time, but oh, oh, oh so good!

title: toll house treatwich recipe
directions: Use the traditional recipe for Toll House cookies on the back of the package; drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Press dough into 2-inch circles.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheets.
Cool completely.

title: spanish cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling water 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain well. Combine butter, sugar, salt, pepper and cracker crumbs.
Stir in green pepper, tomatoes, onion, 1 1/4 cups cheese and hot cauliflower.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meatball sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients, then pour in meatballs.
Warm thoroughly.
Pour into crock-pot and keep warm until time to serve.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: On small pizza pan, flatten cream cheese.
Put chili on top, then put onions on, green chilies and then sprinkle Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 minutes on High in microwave.
Serve with basket of tortilla chips.
(Can make ahead and put in refrigerator.)

title: oyster stew
directions: NOTE:
Omit butter if using part cream for milk.

title: herb tofu
directions: In blender or food processor, place tofu and yogurt.
Add chopped vegetables and salt and pepper to taste.
Place on serving platter with bagels, crackers or pita bread.

title: sorghum cake
directions: Mix well first 2 ingredients.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Stir well. Add last 4 ingredients. Stir well. Pour into 2 deep dish or 3 regular pie crusts. Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: chicken-cheese casserole
directions: Mix egg and dip chicken in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in little oil and place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour mushrooms over chicken.
Cover chicken with cheese.
Pour chicken broth over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, cook 40 minutes at 350°, covered.
Remove cover and cook 15 minutes more or until tender.

title: caramel seven-minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients, except maple flavoring, in top of double boiler (not over heat); beat 1 minute with electric beater to blend.
Place over boiling water on low to medium heat and cook, beating constantly, about 7 minutes.
Do not overcook. Remove from boiling water.
Add maple flavoring and beat 2 more minutes.

title: baked mushroom pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a low, flat, baking pan (do not stack). Mix water with soup; pour over the pork chops.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.

title: gobs
directions: *To get sour milk, add 2 tablespoons of vinegar to milk.

title: spinach casserole with fried onions
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw spinach and drain well, pressing out moisture.
Mix spinach, cheese, artichoke hearts and soup in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in 3/4 of can of onion rings.
Sprinkle remaining onions on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix 1 cup flour and 1 stick oleo.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan for a crust.
Bake about 8 minutes.
Beat together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add large Cool Whip.
Save some Cool Whip for topping.
Put filling in a cool crust.
Mix the instant pudding in separate bowls.
(Use less milk to make it thicker.)
Layer the vanilla, then chocolate.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: moe's rice
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Remove casing from sausage; slice in two and bake sausage until done.
Remove all grease with paper towel. Slice carrots.
Chop peppers.
Blanch carrots, peppers and peas in 4 tablespoons of water in microwave, separately.
Use a large skillet and saute onions in butter until they start to brown.
Add one pint of broth and let simmer.
Stir in package of rice and when rice begins to boil, add second pint of broth and water.
Add fresh squeezed garlic and salt, if desired.
Add curry and orange juice.
Add peppers and carrots.
Let simmer for 12 minutes and add peas.
Break sausage in tiny pieces and add.
Stir constantly. Add additional water as needed.
Serve with chopped olives and green onions on top.

title: garden patch meat loaf for a crowd
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Generously grease 12 cup ring mold. Combine meats in a very large bowl; mix well.
Combine milk, honey, oats, onion soup mix, eggs, basil and pepper in a medium bowl; stir to combine.
Add to meat mixture and mix well.
Pat mixture into prepared pan.
Place on a jelly roll pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Run knife around and carefully unmold on pan.
Brush with catsup and mustard mixture. Return to turned-off oven for 10 minutes until glazed.
Fill center with carrots and peas. Serve with mashed potatoes, if desired.
Makes 16 servings.

title: best lemon pie
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and slowly pour 1/4 cup sugar over pie. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes; cool.

title: ham and cheese appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into rectangles, about 2 x 1 1/2-inches. Makes 36 appetizers.

title: take along butterscotch oat bars
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, eggs and milk in a large mixer bowl. Beat until well blended. Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and soda. Gradually add to liquid mixture. Beat until smooth.
Stir in oats, butterscotch chips, raisins and nuts. Spread into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool. Spread icing over top. Cut into 24 squares.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add chopped cabbage and 1 cup water. Cover; cook until cabbage is soft.
Remove cover and fry until light brown; set aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat, celery, pepper and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let cook until celery and onion are tender.
Add beans and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk.
Mix in bananas and walnuts. Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and sugar for 2 minutes. Gradually add oil and beat 2 minutes.
Add extract.
Alternately fold in flour mixture and zucchini until evenly
moistened.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Do not overmix.
Pour into well-greased or sprayed loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until it tests done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.

title: mixed fruit compote
directions: Combine prunes and apricots in a bowl; set aside.
Heat apple juice with cinnamon stick in small saucepan over medium heat until hot.
Pour over prunes and apricots.
Cover and let stand 8 hours. Remove cinnamon stick and add orange rind and next 5 ingredients; toss gently.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple cheese dish
directions: Pour pineapple into a Pyrex dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese together.
Pour over pineapple.
Mix together melted margarine and crackers; sprinkle over top of cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Delicious warm or cold.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender, but not brown. Add chicken; cook 2 minutes longer. Stir in rice, raisins and seasonings. Mix apricot syrup, soy sauce and sherry with enough broth to make 2 cups. Stir into rice mixture. Bring to a boil. Stir once, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Add apricot halves. Heat thoroughly. Toss lightly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream together the sugar and shortening in a large mixing bowl.
Add slightly beaten eggs, bananas and Bisquick.
Beat until well mixed.
Add nuts to mixture and blend. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan (Pam works well).
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool before slicing.

title: barbecue buffalo on bun
directions: In a large skillet, add onion and brown in oil.
Add meat. Brown and break it up as soon as it cooks.
Add salsa and barbecue sauce to mixture.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Spoon on bun.
Shredded lettuce and cheese are good toppings. Enjoy.

title: fried rice with bacon
directions: Stir-fry rice in hot oil for 1 minute. Add sugar, salt and soy sauce. Stir until heated through. Add eggs, scallions and bacon. Stir to mix and serve.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs in a flat dish.
Melt margarine in a dish.
Dip chicken in margarine and roll in bread crumbs.
Lay flat in baking dish.
Pour remaining margarine over chicken.
Sprinkle chicken seasoning over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Beat in the peanut butter and vanilla.
Add the Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll in nuts, dried beef or parsley.

title: fluffy white rice
directions: Place rice in large bowl. Rinse with water 3 or 4 times or until water is no longer cloudy. Drain.

title: brown rice
directions: Simmer mushrooms and onion in oleo until done.
Combine with rice, consomme, water and salt.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spanish pinto beans
directions: Cook beans until almost done.
Cut potatoes into chunks.
Add potatoes and all other ingredients.
Cook until done.

title: pineapple sponge cake
directions: Put Cool Whip into bottom of pan.
Crumble up 1/2 of cake and stir into Cool Whip.
Add coconut, cherries and pineapple, then other 1/2 of crumbled cake.
Top with additional 8-10 cherries. May top with additional Cool Whip.

title: white house cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugars.
Add oil, egg and vanilla.
Mix together flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Mix with cream mixture, then add Rice Krispies, oats and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
9 dozen or more.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Line
casserole
with
biscuits.
Cover with sour cream and cottage cheese.
Moderately fill dish (2/3 full) with bell peppers, broccoli
and
tomato.
Mix
a
small amount of salad dressing into
vegetables.	Onions may be added.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned lemon filling cake
directions: Cook over low fire until thickens.
Use on cake of your choice.

title: chicken adobo(east indian dish)
directions: Cook chicken in 8 cups water with all ingredients until chicken is done.
Serve chicken and broth over rice.

title: red hot punch
directions: Boil red hots, sugar and water until red hots dissolve.
Add juice, Kool-Aid and 7-Up.
Add enough water to make 2 gallons.

title: green beans with walnut dressing
directions: Wash beans; trim ends.
Bring water to a boil in a pan; add beans.
Cook for 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Combine green onions and next 6 ingredients; pour over green beans and toss gently.
Sprinkle with walnuts; serve hot or cold.
Serves 8.

title: chow-chow(uncooked)
directions: First, grind and drain the tomatoes, cabbage, peppers, onions, celery, lemons and hot peppers.
Mix with other ingredients. Store at room temperature in jars, covered tightly enough to keep sour gnats out.
But do not seal as it will work like sauerkraut. It is good either before or after it works, though the flavor will change.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: In a bowl, place cream cheese; gradually stir in crushed pineapple, pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Cover and chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: fat-free rice and bean casserole
directions: In a 1-quart microwaveable casserole, microwave margarine for 30 seconds to melt. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Stir to combine.
Cover and microwave on High for 2 minutes, stirring once.
Add black-eyed peas, milk, 1 tablespoon water and bay leaf. Microwave on High 2 minutes until mixture is boiling.
Stir in rice.
Cover and microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir in seasoning. Cover and microwave 2 1/2 minutes. Let stand 2 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Remove and discard bay leaf.

title: chicken-fried steak
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; sprinkle on both sides of steaks. Combine egg and 2 tablespoons milk in a shallow dish.
Dip steaks in egg mixture and dredge in cracker crumbs.
Fry steaks in 1/2 inch deep oil until browned.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, turning occasionally.
Remove, drain on paper towel and keep warm.
Drain off drippings, reserving 3 tablespoons in skillet.
Add 3 tablespoons flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add broth and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Stir in hot sauce and Worcestershire to taste.
Serve steaks and gravy on rice or with potatoes.

title: egg-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Slice top off tomato and scoop out pulp without damaging the outer skin.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls in jellyroll pan.
Cook sausage; drain. Crumble sausage onto crescent rolls.
Layer hash browns, mushrooms, onions, green peppers and cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together; pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: southern chess pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Beat in thoroughly eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Best to take out of the oven when the center lightly jiggles.
It will finish cooking on its own.
Serve slightly warm, plain or with whipped cream.

title: christmas tree cake
directions: Bake 24 cupcakes and let cool completely.
Remove paper liners. Frost bottom and sides of cupcakes using white frosting tinted with green food coloring.

title: seafood creole
directions: Prepare roux by heating oil in large skillet and blending in flour on medium heat.
Stir constantly until brown; be careful not to scorch.
Add water slowly and cook until thick and smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Remove bay leaves.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let it stand in refrigerator overnight.
Serve cold.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Let cheese warm to room temperature.
Drain shrimp.
Mix all ingredients.
Fluff with a fork.
Chill and serve.
This is good as a dip with cauliflower or served on crackers.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Add Cheez Whiz while rice is hot.
Saute onion and celery for 5 minutes in margarine.
Cook broccoli.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar; add molasses, water and egg, then add flour and spices.
Drop with teaspoon onto greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Take 1/2 to 3/4 cup cold water and mix with cornstarch until it is smooth.
Have about 1 1/2 cups of water on low heat on stove.
Pour in cornstarch and stir until clear and thick.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and mix.
Pour the remaining water in and mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until it begins to thicken.
Break angel food cake into bite size pieces and add to jello.
You may not need all of the cake.
Stir in strawberries and let congeal.
Top with Dream Whip.
Serves 8 people.

title: finnish apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Resift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to batter alternately with sour cream.
Mix until batter is velvety and pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Insert apples, rounded edge up.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: angel bavarian dessert
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and milk together and bring to boil. Beat and gradually add to custard the 4 egg yolks.
Boil until it coats spoon.
Cool.
Mix gelatin and water and set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add to whipped cream or Cool Whip (3/4 of carton).
Add gelatin, coconut, custard and vanilla.
Crumble cake in a 9 x 14-inch dish; cover with custard mix.
Separate cake with fork and let mix soak through cake.
Store in refrigerator until chilled.
Spread rest of Cool Whip (3/4 carton) on top and sprinkle with 1/4 cup coconut.

title: frosting(sugar free)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cathy's chicken
directions: Melt Shedd's Spread, then
lightly brush on chicken breasts. Roll chicken in crushed crackers and place on foil-lined pan. Cover securely with foil and bake at 425° for about 45 minutes.

title: strawberry carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan. Beat all ingredients except strawberries and glaze in large bowl on low speed 45 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Fold in strawberries; pour into pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Prepare Strawberry Cream Cheese Glaze.
Spoon onto cake.
Refrigerate.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix altogether and bake at 350°.

title: corn scallop
directions: Melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sour cream.
Mix in slightly beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown around edge. Good to take to potluck dinners!

title: mike's mother's "blueberry" muffins
directions: On low speed, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; blend.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Blend 1/2 cup of washed berries into batter.
Now, add the rest of the berries and stir in gently.
Grease muffin pans well with butter all the way to the top of each pan.
Fill batter high; sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°. Makes 12 large muffins.

title: molded raspberry salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Chill until cold. Remove from refrigerator and add lemon-lime; chill until set.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes and combine in large bowl with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add chopped onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Cover with 1/4 cup melted butter mixed with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be fixed ahead and refrigerated overnight before baking.
Delicious.

title: cuban chicken with black bean sauce
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in hot skillet.
Cover, turn down heat and brown for 10 minutes.
Remove chicken to plate.
Add onions, garlic and bell pepper to pan.
Saute for 2 minutes.
Add beans and chicken.
Add enough water to simmer chicken.
Add cayenne to taste.
Cook about 30 minutes or until done.
Serve over hot rice.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix well and serve with chips.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, lemon extract and pineapple juice.
Mix dry ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box, using a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Using a toothpick, make holes in the cake, at 25 to 30.

title: mixed nut bars
directions: Melt butter on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle cake mix over butter. Layer on remaining ingredients, except milk.
Pour milk over layered ingredients.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
(Don't overbake; watch carefully.)

title: shrimp boil
directions: Bring seasoning, garlic, oranges, lemons and onions to a boil.
Add potatoes and corn, boil for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp, boil 2 minutes.
Remove oranges, lemons and garlic cloves.
Serve shrimp, potatoes and corn.

title: ketchup-raisin cookies
directions: Beat butter; add white and brown sugar.
Beat until fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in creamed mixture with ketchup.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until edges are brown.
Brush with lemon glaze while warm.

title: frozen salad
directions: Whip the cream cheese and whipping cream.
Add salad dressing, fruit cocktail, pineapple, cherries and marshmallows and freeze. Keep frozen.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
May decorate with cherries.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl.
Chill.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Stir melted butter into the cracker crumbs.
Put a thin layer in bottom of
buttered
baking dish.
Cover with oysters and sprinkle with salt and
pepper.
Add half oyster juice and milk. Repeat and cover top with remaining crumbs.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, brown sugar and egg yolks in saucepan; mix well.
Add milk, water, butter and salt.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in vanilla. Spoon into pie shell.
Beat egg whites in mixer bowl until soft peaks form.
Add remaining 1/4 cup sugar gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread over top of pie, sealing to edge.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: sour cream salmon loaf
directions: Measure corn flakes and then crush them into crumbs. Drain off half of the liquid of the salmon. Combine all ingredients. Place in a loaf pan and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°. If firmer texture loaf is desired, use less butter or margarine and add one more egg.

title: slush
directions: Mix orange juice and lemonade with 7-Up.
Put in freezer.
Stir every few hours.
Put in glass, pour 7-Up over and drink.

title: orange-glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender but still firm.
Drain.
In preheated skillet, melt butter and blend in brown sugar, orange juice and salt.
Add carrots and toss lightly over low heat until coated.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: *french strawberry pie
directions: Spread cream cheese, blended with sufficient cream to soften, over the bottom of a cooled, baked pie shell.
Place half of the berries in cheese coated pie shell.
Mash remaining berries until juice is well extracted.
Bring to boiling point and slowly stir in sugar and cornstarch, which have been mixed together.
Cook slowly for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool and pour over uncooked berries in baked 9-inch pie shell.
Serve with whipping cream.

title: warabi rice
directions: Cook rice in
the
usual
way.	While
rice is cooking, prepare other ingredients.	Heat oil in frying pan.
Fry iriko in oil until
crispy.	Add
aburage and shiitake; cook about 2 minutes.
Add warabi, kamaboko and salt to taste (should be on the salty
side).
Cook
about
minute.
Do
not
overcook warabi, should be
crunchy.
When
rice
is
done, combine hot rice with warabi mixture in a bowl; mix until well blended.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook ingredients.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese, sour cream and lettuce.
Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs, melted butter, buttermilk and vanilla until well blended.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle tops of both pies heavily with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool.
Pie is wonderful served warm.

title: linda's spaghetti casserole
directions: *Can use 1 jar spaghetti sauce instead.

title: celery casserole
directions: Mix the chopped celery in with the soup.
Add 1/2 cup of water.
Add small can of pimento and pepper lightly.
Mix thoroughly in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs; bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: crab dip
directions: Drain and rinse crab meat.
Mix all ingredients with a fork except crab meat.
Add last and mix well. Bake in small casserole dish 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Great with wheat crackers.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and beat well.
Add vanilla, pecans and chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Use greased, floured tube pan.
Cool 5 minutes and remove.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Stir in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Add mix gradually. Roll out dough to about 1/3-inch thickness, handling as little as possible.
Cut out doughnuts; fry in deep fryer or skillet.
Fry until doughnuts rise to surface and brown each side 1 minute.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine ingredients, mix and form patties.
Fry slowly in butter, turning once, about 7 minutes each side.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve. Great with raw vegetables such as carrots, celery, cauliflower, etc.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine soups, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in zucchini and onion.
Combine stuffing (crumbs and flavor package) with melted butter.
Don't follow package directions.
Spread 1/2 stuffing in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon in mix and cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein Shrimp; chop Garlic fine.
Pour Italian Dressing into a large skillet, add chopped Garlic, add peeled and deveined Shrimp (raw).
Saute Shrimp in covered skillet for 10 minutes or until Shrimp are pink.
Remove from heat.
In a small casserole dish, place Shrimp in casserole dish, then place Cheese over Shrimp (repeat if second layer of Shrimp is used).

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Dump in the undrained crushed pineapple and swirl around to fill corners.
Dump in cherry pie filling and push it around so it is even.
Sprinkle dry cake mix all around to cover.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over mix.
Cut oleo into patties and place on top.
Do not mix.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve just as is or with dab of Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in sauce and water.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and pepper.
Spoon meat sauce over bottom of oblong dish.
Alternate layer of noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella cheese and sauce, ending with sauce.
Cover with plastic and cook in microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Cook 30 minutes more on Medium-low (40% power).
Top with Parmesan cheese and let stand, covered, at least 15 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Roll into meat balls; place in baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cream of sorrel soup(szczaw)
directions: In soup pot, melt butter.
Saute onions and celery over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add sorrel and simmer three minutes. Add chicken broth, potatoes and bay leaves and simmer until potatoes are tender.
In separate pot or bowl, fork-blend sour cream with 3 to 4 tablespoons flour until very smooth, gradually adding a cup of broth at a time (3 to 4 cups).
Stir this mixture into soup and simmer several minutes without boiling.

title: jello pudding cake(yum yum yum!)
directions: Bake cake as instructed on box.
Make lime Jell-O as instructed.
Make red Jell-O as instructed.
Set aside.
Mix instant pudding and Dream Whip with vanilla extract and chill.

title: corn dogs(by flora edwards)
directions: Mix first six ingredients into batter.
Cover hot dogs and drop in hot deep oil.
Cook until brown or done to taste.
(Chop up onions and mix in the batter for hush puppies.
If batter is too thin, add more meal.)

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter in medium bowl until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour, sugar and vanilla, mixing thoroughly.
Blend in potato chips.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly golden, about 10 minutes.
Let cool on baking sheet 5 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Transfer to wire rack and cool thoroughly.

title: cathy's ice cream
directions: Mix and churn until frozen.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown in loaf pan.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Pour in Eagle Brand milk.
Sprinkle on chips, coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes, just long enough to stick together.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cut into small pieces.
Mix soups and water. Mix margarine and stuffing together.
In a dish, layer stuffing, chicken and soup; repeat layers.
Top with stuffing.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cajun shrimp creole
directions: In a 10 inch skillet, heat oil.
Add flour, stir on medium heat until flour begins to brown.
Add onion, bell pepper, garlic, parsley, cayenne, black pepper and salt.
Simmer on medium heat until onion is limp and clear.
Add shrimp, cook until all shrimp are pink.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 20 minutes on low heat.
Serve over rice.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: ala pilaf(low-fat instead of potatoes)
directions: In frypan, melt butter; add vegetables and cracked wheat. Cook and stir until vegetables are tender.
Add seasonings and bouillon broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Delicious.

title: gumdrop fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 2 cups flour, seasonings, eggs and baking soda.
Sift 2 cups flour over fruit and gumdrops.
Add to mixture.
Bake 2 hours in angel food cake pan at 325°.
Put pan of water in oven for moisture.

title: granola crust
directions: Blend
granola well.
Pour into a bowl.
Sprinkle water over the
mixture
until
soft like pie dough.
Press into pie pan. Bake
at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes, until slightly brown. Cool before adding the cooled filling.

title: maple crunch cookies
directions: Cream shortening with syrup and sugar.
Add eggs and continue beating until fluffy.
Measure dry ingredients into sifter.
Mix together twice to blend, then sift all at once into creamed mixture.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pickled vegetables - peppers
directions: Slice
peppers	fairly	thin;
pack in jars.
Add equal parts of	water
in each;
put 1 teaspoon of salt and 4 tablespoons of vinegar on top.
Seal jars.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: *I use powdered buttermilk and whole milk instead of water. Powdered buttermilk can be added to dry ingredients.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle with dill.
Serve with crackers and party rye.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together and cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown ground beef with next 4 ingredients and salt to taste. Drain well.
Pour cooked noodles, ground beef mixture and cheese into large casserole dish.
Pour on enough tomato juice to cover. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, adding more tomato juice if needed.

title: fried apples
directions: Cook and keep stirring until tender.

title: heavenly chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine candy and sweetened condensed milk in a large saucepan; cook over low heat until candy melts. Stir constantly. Cool, stirring occasionally.
Add about 1 quart milk to candy mixture. Beat until well blended.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer can. Stir in chocolate syrup.
Add enough milk to fill freezer container to within 4-inches from top.
Freeze.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine turkey or beef, package of taco seasoning, 1/2 cup Mexican salsa, bread crumbs and egg whites.
Pour 1/2 cup salsa on top.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: best-ever beef stew
directions: Trim meat and cut into 2-inch cubes. In a large plastic bag, combine flour, garlic, salt and pepper. Shake meat in bag, 3 to 4 pieces at a time, to coat.
Melt butter in large stew pan and brown meat on all sides on low heat.
When browned, add water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add bouillon cubes.
Add bay leaf and simmer 1/2 hour. Add chopped vegetables. Increase heat and cook an additional 1 hour.
Thicken with flour and water.
Heat through and serve.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; roll in flour.
Fry in oil approximately 10 minutes on each side over medium heat.
Salt to taste.
Drain off oil; remove from heat.
In separate container, mix mushroom soup with 1 cup water and diced onion.
Place chicken back on stove on low heat.
Pour mixture over chicken and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, until mixture thickens.
Serve topped with sauce.
Serves 4.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in an airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup milk with 1 cup water (boiling) per serving.
Yields 4 quarts dry milk or 50 servings.

title: foolproof cornstarch gravy
directions: Pour off drippings and return 2 tablespoons to roasting pan. Stir in 2 cups liquid.
Cook over medium heat, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Remove from heat.
Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup water until smooth; stir into liquid in pan.
Add seasonings.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute. Makes about 2 cups.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and add in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cubed cheese and stir until cheese in melted.
Mix macaroni and cheese sauce and pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes (or until light golden brown on top) at 350.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven.
Add apples and onion; saute. Add cabbage, wine, cloves and sugar.
Pour vinegar over cabbage first to prevent it from losing red color.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: In large container, mix orange juice, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Add sugar, hot water and salt to mixture. Stir.
Add water, ginger ale and ice cream.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Spray a 12-well muffin tin 3 times with the vegetable oil.
Put the egg whites in a large mixing bowl and whisk until frothy.
Whisk in the maple syrup, orange juice and milk.
Add the vanilla, cinnamon, allspice, cloves, nutmeg and orange zest.
Whisk to blend.
Stir in the oats, flour and baking powder with a wooden spoon.
Fold in the pecans and dried cranberries.
Fill the muffin tin with the batter (each cup should be approximately 2/3 full).
Bake for about 20 minutes, until the muffins are firm in the center.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: hot bacon and swiss dip
directions: Blend all together.
Put in glass pie pan.
Microwave until cheese melts. Serve with Triscuits or bread sticks.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until golden.
Add drained clams and saute for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for about 15 minutes or until half the liquid evaporates.
Season to taste.
Serve over linguine.
Top with grated cheese.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup of the evaporated milk in microwave-safe dish and melt, stirring occasionally, until all are melted.
Combine cake mix, butter and remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk in bowl.
Beat 2 minutes.
Spread 1/2 batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together salad oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add sifted ingredients to first mixture and blend together.
Add diced apples and chopped nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool bread slightly, then place on aluminum foil while still hot.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Wrap tightly in foil until cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the water and soups.
Put rice in 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup mixture over rice.

title: onion tart
directions: Heat butter in heavy saucepan and stir in thinly sliced onions. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until onions are almost transparent.
Remove from heat and cool thoroughly.
Stir in mushrooms.
Stir in sour cream, mixed with 4 tablespoons of sherry and three well-beaten eggs.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, nutmeg, thyme and cloves.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with flaky piecrust.
Fill shell with onion mixture and top with bacon squares.
Bake at 350° until filling is firm and crust lightly browned.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple crunch salad(sugar free)
directions: Pour boiling water over Jell-O, stir until dissolved.
Add apple juice and cinnamon.
Place in refrigerator until slightly jelled, then add rest of chopped ingredients.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pauly's fish
directions: Marinate fillets in Italian dressing for 1 hour.
Take out. Spray broiler pan with Pam.
Pour melted butter on fish.
Sprinkle with seasoning *(can be found in seasoning section of grocery). Broil 15 to 20 minutes, no need to turn.
Squirt with fresh lemon before serving.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Brown together ground beef, bacon and onion.
Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two 9-inch pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mai-tai fruit salad
directions: Cut pineapple in half lengthwise and remove fruit.
Cut this into chunks and combine with other fruit.
Combine other ingredients for dressing and pour over fruit.
Toss gently and spoon back into the shells.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli-stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brush the skins of the potatoes with the margarine and score them down the middle lengthwise.
Bake them for 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Steam broccoli stalks for 6 to 8 minutes or just until tender.
Chop finely.
Carefully slice the potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop the flesh into a bowl. (Reserve the skins.)
Add broccoli, 1/2 cup of the cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Mash until the mixture is pale green with dark flecks.
Spoon the mixture into the potato skins and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Place on a baking sheet and bake for 10 minutes. Heat broiler and broil potatoes for 1 minute, or until the tops are golden brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, syrup, sugar, chips, batter and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Stir pecans in and pour in crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Add all ingredients and stir just enough to moisten.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chicken. Roll in flour and brown on both sides in skillet with oil. Remove from oil and place in baking dish. Mix soup, rice and water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Beat 4 minutes.
Pour in Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Needs no icing.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix sliced cucumbers and salt.
Cover with cold water (ice water, if possible) and let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Bring vinegar and spices to boiling.
Add vegetables; reduce flame and simmer for a few minutes but not until cucumbers are soft.
Pack in hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch of headspace.
Adjust for lids. Process in boiling water bath canner.
Makes 7 pints.

title: mom's french onion soup
directions: In a large, deep pan, cook onions in margarine until golden. Add water, bouillon cubes, Worcestershire sauce, paprika and pepper.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion, pepper and hamburger in shortening.
In large saucepan, combine hamburger mixture, tomato paste, sauce and soup. Mix well, adding a little water if too thick.
Add garlic salt, sugar and cheese.
Mix well.
Let simmer for about 45 minutes. Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: mexican hot dip
directions: Crumble beef in 2-quart glass casserole.
Stir in green pepper and taco mix.
Cover; microwave on High power 5 to 6 minutes, or until beef is no longer pink.
Stir and break meat apart.
Stir in cheese, beans, tomato sauce and relish.
Microwave, uncovered, on High power for 5 to 9 minutes, or until hot and cheese melts, stirring twice.
Garnish with green onions and sour cream.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry hamburger in butter with onion.
When done, add rice cooked in water.
Add to meat.
Add tomatoes, salt and spice.
If needed, add more water.
Bake until brown.

title: herbed meat loaves
directions: Combine egg, stuffing mix, onion soup mix and 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce.
Add raw ground beef.
Mix well.
Shape into 5 small loaves.
Cok covered for 8 to 10 minutes or until meat loaves are no longer pink.
Spoon over remaining barbecue sauce on loaves.

title: fry bread pudding
directions: Split fry bread into thin halves.
Caramelize sugar; add water to make a syrup.
Layer fry bread, raisins and cheese.
Pour syrup over mixture and bake in 300° oven until all syrup is absorbed.

title: marshmallow frosting
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk and cool.
Add whipped cream and vanilla; mix.

title: cheese-paprika potatoes
directions: In baking dish, pour enough oil in to be able to coat each peeled potato. Use potatoes the same size. Rub each potato with oil. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, cheese and paprika.
Turn once during baking and sprinkle the other side.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: german beef rouladen(international cuisine)
directions: Lay meat out on cutting board.
Spread thin layer of mustard. From left to right, place a piece of bacon, a pickle spear, then a couple of thin pieces of onion.
Repeat bacon, pickle and onion all the way across the length of the steak.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Roll up in tight roll; secure with toothpicks.
When rolls complete, braise in 5-quart Dutch oven and 2 tablespoons oil.
When rolls are nicely browned, add water to cover bottom (about 1 inch) and simmer meat on medium to low for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until tender.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops. Combine water, soup, onions and salt. Bring to a boil. In casserole, layer rice, soup and chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low calorie french dressing
directions: Add garlic to vinegar; let stand for 20 minutes.
Strain. Combine salt, pepper, paprika and sugar in a jar.
Add tomato juice, water, vinegar and oil.
Cover; shake vigorously.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake again before using.
Yield:
1 cup.

title: green beans almondine
directions: Wash beans and break off ends.
Break beans into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place beans in 2-quart casserole.
Stir water and salt until it is dissolved.
Mix with beans.
Microwave on High until beans are tender-crisp, 9 to 13 minutes.
Drain.
Mix in almonds, margarine, nutmeg and pepper until butter is melted. Microwave on High until heated through.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift together remaining ingredients. Add to butter and sugar mixture. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: creamy horseradish rice
directions: Combine rice with remaining ingredients.
Stir well.

title: sweet potato and apple bake
directions: Grease casserole with part of margarine.
Layer potatoes, dot with margarine and sprinkle with brown sugar and layer with apple slices.
Repeat, ending with potatoes, margarine and brown sugar. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° or until potatoes are tender and browned.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chinese beef and cabbage soup
directions: In bowl, combine soy sauce and oil; add beef and tangerine peel, tossing to coat.
Set mixture aside for 30 minutes, stirring now and then.
In a kettle, bring broth to a boil.
Add cabbage, mushrooms and sugar and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Add beef mixture; cook 5 minutes (longer, if desired or until done).
Serve at once.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix everything in order listed and put in mold greased with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate.

title: aunt viola's clam pie(an old eastern l.i. tradition)
directions: Slice potatoes and onions and parboil 15 minutes in water barely to cover.
Drain.
To potatoes and onions, add butter; sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Add clams, clam juice and cream or milk; stir and bring to a boil.
Put in pastry-lined pie pan.
Cover with top crust; seal edges and slit top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 400°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: In a large kettle, combine gelatin with boiling water, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Then fold in strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and walnuts.
Turn half of strawberry mixture into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate until firm. Spread top with sour cream.
Gently spoon on rest of strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: super simple mexican dip
directions: In bottom of 6 x 9-inch (or 8 x 8-inch) baking dish, spread cream cheese.
On top of cream cheese, spread can of chili.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Microwave until Cheddar cheese melts (approximately 5 minutes on High).
Serve with nacho chips.

title: toll house pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs until foamy.
Beat in the flour and the sugars until well blended and thick.
Add melted margarine.
Fold in chocolate chips and pecans and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: sour cream and cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve as a topping for baked potatoes or as a side dish.
If the dressing is too thick, add a small amount of milk.
If it is too thin, add more vinegar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cover.
Makes 1 big casserole or 2 small ones, which can be frozen to be used at a later time.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onions until tender; drain.
Melt oleo in saucepan; combine flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook until bubbly; add cream cheese.
Stir well.
Combine broccoli and onions in 1-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over; mix.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cap'n crunch candy
directions: Put cereal in big bowl.
Melt bark.
Pour over cereal and peanuts.
Mix and cool.
Break apart.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then add frozen strawberries.
Beat until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Add angel food cake, torn in small pieces, about the size of a quarter.
Mix well with a spoon.
Mold into angel food cake pan and refrigerate. Frost cake with Cool Whip.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: veggie bars
directions: On a cookie sheet, press both cans of crescent rolls flat so all the seams are closed. Brush with beaten egg. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
If dough puffs up while baking, flatten with spoon. Let crust cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: apricot chicken
directions: *Boneless, skinless tenderloins work best.

title: easy dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add flour, whipping cream and vanilla.
Flour and grease cake pan and bake at 375° until done.
Test with toothpick and if it comes out clean, it is done.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.

title: mike's pizza
directions: Follow directions on pizza crust mix.
Cover with Ragu; mix bell pepper and onion; spread over crust.
Shred cheeses and spread over crust.
Fry bacon (or cook other meat) and crumble over top. Bake at 500° for 10 minutes.

title: ratatouille
directions: In Dutch oven, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add the undrained tomatoes, thyme, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Slice eggplant in half lengthwise, then crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Add eggplant, zucchini, pepper and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Uncover; simmer 15 minutes longer.

title: sugarless apple cookies
directions: Soften raisins and dates on stove with a bit of water and cool.
Combine all ingredients. Form in balls and place on cookie sheets. Bake at 375°
for 10 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: garbage bag snack mix
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter in microwave 2 minutes.
Pour over Rice Chex mix.
Mix and place in clean small garbage bag.
Add powdered sugar and shake.
Lay out on small garbage bag to dry overnight.
Put in airtight container.

title: creamy asparagus soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in onion and celery.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken broth; cook 5 to 7 minutes or
until thoroughly heated, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in asparagus.
Puree asparagus mixture.
Return to saucepan; stir in half and half.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes or until slightly thickened and thoroughly heated.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: In a large bowl or dishpan, mix the cracker crumbs, fruit, coconut and pecans.
In a separate bowl, melt marshmallows and milk together.
Pour over the dry mixture.
Mix together and form into a cake.
This will make a large 7 pound cake or several small ones. This cake will seem dry while mixing, but no additional moisture is needed.
Store covered in the refrigerator.
Will keep well.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat sugar and butter until creamy. Beat in egg until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in chopped Butterfinger chips. Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 11 to 13 minutes. Remove cookies quickly.
Serves 30.

title: candy
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Mix.
Pour into a greased dish.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar with 1 quart of water.
Add lemonade and pineapple juice.
Add 5 quarts of water.
Freeze to slush in a 2 1/2-gallon container (about 9 hours).
Add 1-quart 7-up or ginger ale right before serving.
Makes 35 cups of punch.

title: shrimp fritters
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix in egg yolks and shrimp. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Drain and serve.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Place mushrooms in casserole.
Melt butter with marjoram, scallion greens, salt and pepper.
Add bouillon and wine.
Stir and pour over mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin bake
directions: Place pork tenderloin in glass dish.
Mix rest of ingredients for marinade.
Pour over meat.
Marinate for 6 to 8 hours or overnight; turn occasionally.

title: holiday cranberry punch
directions: Combine orange juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add cranberry juice; mix well.
Chill.
Spoon scoops of sherbet on top of punch.
Add ginger ale; gently stir to blend.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; add.
Combine mix.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Note: Cubed ham is also good in this, but is optional.

title: soda cracker snack
directions: Cut bacon strips in half.
Wrap 1/2 bacon strip around each saltine cracker, lapping on top.
Place in baking pan.
Sprinkle light brown sugar over top of all.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes or until bacon is done.
Place on brown paper to absorb grease, then transfer to serving plate.

title: dot's five flavor pound cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco, sugar, eggs, cake flour, baking powder and milk.
Add flavorings.
Blend together well until smooth.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and combine with drained pineapple, 1 cup chopped nuts, bell pepper, onion and salt.
Chill well.
Then form into a ball and roll in remaining nuts.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Toss the corn flake crumbs with melted butter until well mixed. Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, rice, celery, mayonnaise, almonds, soup, onion and chestnuts.
Blend.
Turn into an unbuttered shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cornflake topping.
At this point, the casserole may be frozen or refrigerated until next day, or baked at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot, bubbly and crisp.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt cubed cheeses over low heat (a microwave works well at 1/2 to 3/4 power setting).
Add next 4 ingredients.
Start adding Tabasco sauce until dip is hot enough, keeping in mind that it gets hotter as it stands.
Serve in crock-pot or chafing dish with tortilla chips.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook fettuccine.
Heat butter and cream in a small pan until butter melts.
Add Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Add crabmeat, scallops or shrimp and serve over fettuccine.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place four fillets skinned side up on a flat surface.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Blend crabmeat, egg yolk, parsley and breadcrumbs in a bowl.
Center equal portions of filling on fillets.
Spread out, leaving slightly more on edges. Top with remaining fillets skinned side down.
Press lightly around the sides.
Grease a baking dish and arrange fillets in it. Sprinkle shallots over fillets and pour melted butter over fillets. Pour wine over fillets.
Place the baking dish on the stove and bring wine to a boil.
Let simmer about 15 seconds.
Place under broiler.
Broil approximately 6 to 8 minutes, turning dish to prevent burning.

title: smokey mountain pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Cream with eggs and sugar with mixer.
Add vinegar.
Stir in the rest.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg.
Add soda, flour and salt, which have been mixed together.
Add a few drops of hot water and mix until well blended.
Add morsels and vanilla. Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: date balls
directions: When cool, shape into balls and roll in coconut.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, reserving one cup of tomato sauce to heat and serve with meat loaf.
Bake in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings (290 calories per serving).

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice thinly the potatoes and place in a casserole dish.
Thinly slice onion and pepper and mix with the potato slices.
Add salt and freshly ground pepper to taste.
Trim excess fat off the chops and lay chops on top of the vegetables.
Add milk to top of potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: grits and sausage casserole
directions: Cook grits in bouillon.
Add salt.
Cook sausage until crumbly; drain on paper towels.
Mix sausage with grits.
Add butter, milk, eggs and 1/4 cup of the grated cheese.
Mix well. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: roasting ears
directions: Shuck, clean and wash each ear of corn, being careful to leave shucks attached.
Butter, salt and pepper and replace shucks. Wrap in foil and roast directly over hot coals for 20 minutes, turning ear one-quarter every 5 minutes.

title: apple carrot cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Blend thoroughly. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture and mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and wax papered 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until center of cake is firm to touch.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and finish cooling on cake racks. Frost with Pecan Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: beans, beans, beans
directions: Fry hamburger, bacon and onions and drain.
Put in casserole or Dutch oven.
Add beans.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cornbread mix, butter, eggs, whole kernel corn, cream-style corn and sour cream in bowl.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy chicken noodle dinner
directions: Cook noodles.
In separate pan, heat chicken soup, water and chunky white chicken.
Add seasoning.
Can be mixed with noodles or served separately.

title: baked fresh asparagus
directions: Put butter in a shallow 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Arrange spears in dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over spears. Cover and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Take out to cool, then take chicken off the bone. Put cream of chicken soup in.
Bring to a boil.
Put rice, cook until done, then put chicken in.
Salt to your taste.

title: copper pennies
directions: Layer carrots.
Sprinkle salt and pepper, the onion and green peppers.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over layers.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator.
Let stand overnight.
The dressing is good on tossed salad.
Serves 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add flour and soda.
Mix well. Stir in mashed bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: italian hot dog
directions: Cook potatoes and hot dogs in oil, until done. Saute onions & peppers. Place in sub roll in the following order. Roll, mustard, onions, peppers, hot dog, potatoes, ketchup.

title: banana punch
directions: Mash bananas and blend in 2 cups water.
Set aside.
In a large container, blend 3 cups sugar and 4 cups water.
Add the pineapple juice, orange juice and 2 cups water.
Stir in bananas and juice of lemons.
Freeze in small containers.
Remove from freezer 2 1/2 hours before serving.
Place in a large punch bowl. Add 7-Ups.
Blend to make ice slush.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross on each cookie with fork prongs that have been dipped in water.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute, then remove.

title: microwaved chicken
directions: Arrange the chicken breasts in a large Corning Ware dish that has been spread with margarine.
Tilt lid for first 6 minutes. Add the water at the beginning. Cover completely and cook 8 more minutes or until done. Turn dish once during cooking.

title: wild rice with mushrooms and almonds
directions: Wash and drain rice.
Melt butter in large skillet; add rice, almonds, onion and mushrooms.
Cook and stir until almonds are golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 325°.
Pour rice mixture in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat chicken broth to boiling; stir into rice mixture.
Cover tightly.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender and fluffy.

title: tortellini
directions: Cook tortellini in 3-4 chicken bouillon cubes, 1 Tbsp. oil for 7-10 minutes.

title: iced tea
directions: Bring tea bags and water to a boil.
Let stand until cold.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Set in fridge to keep.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Brown onion in skillet with margarine on medium heat.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, ketchup and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add wieners (optional, can cut wieners in half) and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: southwest chili
directions: Cut beef into cubes, heat oil in Dutch oven.
Put cubed meat into oil and stir to just brown.
Add curry, oregano and garlic. Stir.
Combine chili and flour, add to meat, then stir in the beef broth.
Blend well, simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Check for taste after an hour or so, more chili powder may be desired.

title: stuffed crab
directions: Saute chopped onion and celery in butter.
Add crab meat.
Add evaporated milk; add well beaten eggs.
Cook for about 15 minutes over low heat.
Add bread crumbs until desired thickness obtained. Season with salt, red pepper, parsley flakes and green onion tops. Add more butter if needed.
Place mixture in artificial crab shells.
Sprinkle with dry bread crumbs and bake at 375° until hot. (Freezes good for future use.)

title: gooey butter squares
directions: Mix together and fold into 9 x 13 pan.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Put all ingredients, except potatoes and carrots, into casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 to 3 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Cook for another hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Bake chicken breasts, cool, cut into cubes.
Mix together both cans of soup, broth, Ro-Tel and onion in large bowl.
Place 1/2 bag of doritos into bottom of greased casserole dish.

Place cubed chicken on top of doritos; pour soup mixture over chicken and doritos, slice velveeta cheese and place on top of soup mixture crush other 1/2 bag of doritos and cover the top of casserole. Bake in oven at 325° about 30 minutes or until bubbles up and cheese is melted.

title: hawaiian ham salad pitas
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients, except pita bread and lettuce.
Refrigerate to chill.
Fill pockets with ham and shredded lettuce.

title: broccoli-cheddar meatloaf
directions: Crush 12 crackers, mix with beef, onion, 2 Tbsp. chili sauce, parsley and egg. Pat meat mixture into 12 x 8 inch rectangle on waxed paper. Reserve 2 Tbsp. cheese; sprinkle remaining cheese and broccoli onto meat mixture. Coarsely break remaining 12 crackers. Sprinkle over broccoli. Press lightly into meat mixture. Roll meat into a jelly roll fashion and seal ends. Place loaf into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes. During last 5 minutes of baking, spread remaining 2 Tbsp. chili sauce over meatloaf; sprinkle with reserved cheese.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter and sugar together.
Beat well and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
When cooled, cut into squares.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Let cool completely.
Combine the remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Pour marinade over vegetables.
Stir gently.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hawaiian bread dip
directions: Chop beef into small pieces.
Mix everything together.
Pull out bread to make a bowl and place pieces of bread around bread. Pour dip into bread.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Seal perforations. Bake at 350° until done.
Mix together the cream cheese, dill weed, mayonnaise and garlic or onion powder.
Spread on baked crust. Finely chop the salad vegetables. Sprinkle over pizza and top with Mozzarella cheese. Press down into cream cheese mixture. Serve!

title: alouise's sauerkraut, sausage and dumplings
directions: Cook sauerkraut in water.
Drain; set aside.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Add cooked sauerkraut.
Cook sausage (boil); remove sausage.
Cut into bite size pieces and add to sauerkraut mixture.

title: maple butter
directions: Combine butter and syrup in blender or electric mixer. Process until well blended.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain 1 cup of juice from each can of fruit and add 4 tablespoons Tang.
Mix with puddings and cook until it boils.
Add canned fruit and bananas to cooked mixture and chill overnight, if possible.
(Other fruits may be substituted if desired.)

title: easy seafood newburg
directions: Chop a small bunch of green onions.
In a large frypan or Dutch oven, melt butter. Saute crab meat, shrimp, scallops and onions about 10 minutes until onions are translucent.
Add milk, cream of shrimp soup and wine.
Heat thoroughly and then add the peas.
Cover and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Serve over rice or thin noodles.
This recipe is very easy, yet tastes special. Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 of stuffing in 13 x 10-inch casserole.
Heat 1/2 cup butter and water.
Pour over mixture.
Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and spread over stuffing.

title: twinkie pudding
directions: Split Twinkies in half lengthwise.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread pudding, then layer remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: scones
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients into a bowl.
Rub in butter; mix in enough milk to make a soft but not sticky dough.
Turn the dough onto a floured surface; knead it lightly.
Roll the dough out to a thickness of about 3/4-inch; cut as many scones as possible, using a 2 1/2-inch round cutter.
Gather up the scraps; re-roll them to cut out more scones.
Bake at 425° on a cookie sheet for 10 minutes, or until well risen and golden brown.
Cool on a wire tray.
Makes 8.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Then add sour milk or buttermilk.
Then add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, brown sausage.
Add onions; cook until clear.
Drain off any excess fat.
Add wild rice to sausage; cook according to package directions.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Microwave sugar and corn syrup on High 4 minutes.
Mix in peanuts; microwave 3 to 4 minutes until light brown.
Mix in butter and vanilla well.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto greased pan.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: green rice
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onions and celery in it until tender. Cook broccoli for half the time listed on package.
Cook rice as usual, until done.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat until margarine has melted.

title: celery soup
directions: In a nonstick pan, heat celery.
Cover and cook on medium heat until crunchy (about 5 minutes).
Dissolve chicken soup in water; add celery, onion powder and pepper.
Heat soup on medium heat for about 10 minutes to blend all ingredients.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: In saucepan, bring 2 cups water to boil; add butter and oatmeal.
Simmer 1 minute.
Remove to a large bowl and let cool to 120° to 130°.
Heat the remaining water to 120° to 130°; add yeast. To the oatmeal mixture, add 1/2 flour.
Mix well.
Add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured surface and knead 6 to 8 minutes, or until smooth and elastic.
Add additional flour if necessary.
Place dough in greased bowl and turn once.
Cover and let rise until double (1 hour).
Punch dough in half, divide and shape each half into balls.
Place 1-inch apart in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and let rise until double, 40 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until golden brown.
Add water, bouillon cubes, Worcestershire sauce, paprika and pepper.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with croutons and Mozzarella cheese.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cut the potatoes up and cook in a little water about 1/2 hour or until soft.
Mash and add the butter, sugar and flavoring.
Mix well.
Add pecans and raisins.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Put the marshmallows on top and return to oven about 5 more minutes. If there is any souffle left at the end of the meal, be sure to pick the leftover marshmallows off before reheating.

title: snowflakes
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Pour over Crispix cereal.
Mix until cereal is well coated.
Take confectioners sugar and pour into a brown paper bag.
Add cereal mixture and shake until covered.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
Mix pudding, milk and sugar thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer, starting with crackers, half the mixture, crackers, half the mixture and crackers.
Top with icing and let refrigerate for at least 24 hours. Great!

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Do not brown meat.
Add celery, tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Mix with cooked spaghetti, then pour in baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: anise snaps
directions: Sift together, flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt, (several times). Cream butter and sugar until light. Add eggs, then Anise seed. Chill until firm enough to shape. Shape into small balls an inch in diameter. Sprinkle more anise seed on greased baking sheet and place dough balls far apart. Bake in hot oven, at 400 degrees for 8 minutes.

title: rhubarb wine
directions: Put
rhubarb into crock and pour boiling water over it. Cover and
let
stand
for
24 hours.
Strain and reheat; add sugar, raisins and lemons.
When lukewarm, add one half yeast cake, dissolved in a little water.
Keep well covered for four weeks, stirring
often.
Strain
and
filter,
then
place in bottles and completely seal after fermenting has stopped.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Wrap chicken breasts in foil and bake at 400° until tender, about 1 hour.
Cool and debone, and save broth.
Cut chicken into strips.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 or 3 rounded teaspoonfuls per cup.
Add boiling water.

title: nagyanya kaposzta(grandmother cabbage)
directions: Begin to saute onion in butter or oil, then add ground beef, salt, paprika and black pepper.
When onions are sauteed and meat is lightly browned, remove from fire; drain excess fat and set aside.
In a 4-quart casserole with cover, begin a layering first with cabbage, then meat, repeating until meat and cabbage are used, finishing with a layer of cabbage on top.
Pour the condensed tomato soup over the layered casserole; cover and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until cabbage is tender.
Serve with white mashed potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening (butter) and sugar.
Mix flour with soda, then add eggs, bananas and milk.
Combine with creamed mixture and fold in nuts.
Bake about 1 hour at 300°.
Use 2 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: english mincemeat(5 pounds)
directions: Wash jam jars thoroughly.
Chop or coarsely mince raisins, sultanas (white raisins), almonds and apples and mixed peels into a bowl.
Stir in currants with sugar, suet and spices.
Mix all ingredients together with sherry, lemon rind and juice.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
In another large bowl, layer pudding, bananas and cookies until all pudding is used.
Start with pudding and end with pudding.

title: mexican dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with sour cream and taco seasoning; spread mixture in a shallow dish (pie plate works well).
Top with the veggies and cheese.
Refrigerate.
Serve with taco or corn chips.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown onion.
Add soup and frozen hash browns.
Combine sour cream and grated cheese.
Spray a casserole dish with Pam and put in potato and onion mixture.
Top with sour cream and grated cheese.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top of sour cream and cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until very crisp and golden brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Then mix next five ingredients and pour over crust and bake 20 minutes more.

title: cranberry pork roast
directions: Place pork roast in crock-pot.
In a medium bowl mash cranberry sauce.
Stir in sugar, cranberry juice, mustard and cloves.
Pour over roast.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove roast and keep warm.

title: scalloped fish
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan over medium heat; saute onions until tender.
Stir in bread crumbs and toss.
Remove and set aside.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in skillet; stir in flour and cook 1 to 2 minutes, until smooth.
Slowly add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 3 minutes. Add tuna and sherry; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Stir until blended.
Spread half of tuna mixture in buttered shallow baking dish; cover with half of bread crumbs.
Top with remaining tuna and bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: halloween pizza
directions: Place pizza on baking sheet.
Arrange olives in a circle around edge of pizza.
Cut a nose, eyes and mouth out of red peppers.
Cut a stem and eyebrows out of green pepper.
Make a jack-o'-lantern face on pizza.
Bake according to package directions.

title: tortellini with no-cook tomato sauce
directions: In deep, 4-quart saucepan over high heat, bring 2 quarts water to boil; add tortellini.
Cook 8 minutes, stirring occasionally until tender.
Meanwhile, cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch dices, place in large bowl.
Finely chop basil and parsley; crush garlic.
Add herbs and garlic to bowl with tomatoes.
Gently stir in oil, vinegar, salt and pepper to mix well.
Drain tortellini and toss with tomato mixture.
Serve with grated Romano or Parmesan cheese.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix all other ingredients until light and fluffy.
Add about 1/3 of the flour mixture at a time and mix well after each addition.
Chill dough, shape into balls, place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pudding
directions: Cream butter and add sugar; stir until sugar is blended into butter evenly and smoothly.
Beat egg yolks and add juice of lemon; add to butter mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into butter mixture.
Split ladyfingers in half and using half of them, line the bottom of an 8 x 10-inch Pyrex dish.
Put half the butter mixture over the ladyfingers; crumble the macaroons and spread over the mixture in the pan.
Add the remaining half of the butter mixture; spread remaining ladyfingers on top.
Refrigerate overnight; top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Serves 12.

title: yam-pineapple casserole
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Place 1/2 of the mixture in a buttered baking dish.
Cover with marshmallows.
Add remaining mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; dot with marshmallows.
Place under broiler until brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bar cookies
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over oleo. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Buy fresh shrimp and clean them, then cook the shrimp in butter for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Put mushrooms, onion and green pepper in same pan, lower heat and cook 10 minutes.
Then stir in the salt, tomato paste, chili powder and cream.
Heat just long enough to heat all the way through.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate delight dessert
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until tan.
Cool.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Boil for 60 seconds.
Remove from heat and quickly add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper. Chill 30 minutes.
(May use 1 cup coconut instead of nuts.)

title: cherry marshmallow dessert
directions: Crush graham crackers and add melted butter and sugar. Reserve 2 tablespoons.
Press rest firmly into 8 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Whip cream and add marshmallows carefully.
Put 1/2 of mixture on chilled crust.
Cover with fruit pie filling.
Add remaining marshmallow mixture.
Top with reserved crumbs. Refrigerate overnight.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix
pineapple	and juice with jello in boiler and heat until dissolved.	Let
cool and add buttermilk and Cool Whip. Congeal.

title: taco dip
directions: In oblong glass dish, layer 12 ounce can refried beans, layer of sour cream, layer sliced cheese and layer mild sauce on top. Microwave or bake until cheese has melted.
Serve with plain or nacho cheese chips (Doritos).

title: caramel icing
directions: Cream 1 1/2 boxes of sugar with butter.
Add 3/4 cup of whipping cream.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil two minutes. Place in sink of cold water.
Beat to desired thickness.
Spread on favorite cake layers.

title: pineapple banana cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
In another bowl combine oil, pineapple and juice, vanilla, eggs, bananas and nuts.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir to blend; do not beat.
Pour into a 9-inch greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake is done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: clam sauce for linguini
directions: Place butter, onion, parsley and fennel seed in 12-cup casserole.
Cover and microwave 3 minutes on High.
Add mushrooms and season.
Continue microwaving 3 minutes, covered.
Sprinkle in flour and mix until well incorporated.
Season with paprika.
Pour in chicken stock and reserved clam juice.
Microwave 7 minutes, uncovered, stirring twice during cooking time.
Mix in clams and incorporate cream.
Let stand, uncovered, on counter.
Spoon sauce over hot linguini and serve at once.
Cooking time:
13 minutes.

title: collard greens
directions: Wash and chop collard greens.
Place in a large pot and cover with water.
Simmer for 45 minutes; more water can be used if needed.
After 45 minutes, add rest of ingredients.
Stir well. Cover.
Simmer for 1 hour or until greens are tender.

title: wikiwiki walk-away desserts
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature to soften.
Use mixer to gradually blend in 1/2 cup milk; add remaining milk, drained pineapple and pudding.
Beat 1 minute and chill.
Serve in cones. Makes 8 servings.

title: wacky cake(super moist)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Put together all wet ingredients in another bowl.
Add to dry ingredients and beat for 2 minutes on high. Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: In bowl, place flour, salt, sugar and Crisco, then add water. Dough will need very little handling.
Makes 3 pie shells.

title: how to fry bologna for tasha from trina
directions: Get a frying pan. Spray pan with oil to cover bottom.
Place pan on stove eye and turn stove to #5 (fry).
Place bologna in oil and watch it!
When it starts sizzling, take a fork and flip it. Now do the other side.
Enjoy!

title: pickled turnips
directions: Peel and wash turnips; cut into quarters or slices.
Pack pieces into a clean jar, placing pieces of raw beet between layers.
Dissolve salt in water and stir in vinegar.
Cover the vegetables with liquids.
Seal jar tightly.
Store in a warm place for 10 days; then they will be ready to eat.
If desired, once ready, should be refrigerated.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar.
Sift together flour and cocoa and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 11 x 14-inch pan.
