Bake at 350° for about 14 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Open and drain cans of asparagus spears and place spears in bottom of baking dish.
Pat lightly with butter.
Grate onion very fine and blend together with soup and the cheese.
Crumble cheese crackers on top and pat with butter.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Remove foil and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in balls about size of quarter. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° about 12 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Brown sausage with chopped onion. Drain.
Add chicken broth and oregano.
Add to cooked rice.

title: michigan dressing
directions: Adjust ingredients to taste; chill.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: baby food cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salad oil.
Add baby food.
Sift flour, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add to baby food mixture.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2 - inch baking pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine ingredients in large bowl, putting in nuts and chips last. Mixture will be stiff.
Press evenly in pan.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes until set.
Cool completely and cut into bars.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and evaporated milk in mixing bowl until smooth and creamy.
Stir in crab meat, grated onion, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt, mixing well.
Cover and chill thoroughly to blend flavors.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Mix sugar, water and Karo and boil until it forms a hard ball. Beat into stiffly beaten egg white.
Add vanilla and nuts and beat until ready to drop on wax paper.

title: turkey hash bake
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
In skillet, cook ground turkey and onion until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
In bowl, combine turkey mixture, potato, evaporated milk, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, sage, 3/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Turn mixture into a 1-quart casserole.

title: swedish coffee cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl (cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, salad oil and water).
Beat for 10 minutes.
Pour 1/3 batter into greased tube pan.
Swirl 1/2 of dry ingredients (sugar, cocoa and cinnamon) into the pan and repeat until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool right side up and frost with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together.
Stir in peanut butter. Add dry ingredients, a little at a time, mixing well.
Make small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with back of fork and decorate by pressing morsels lightly on top.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: rolls
directions: Into a large bowl, combine 2 1/4 cups flour, salt, sugar and yeast.
Mix at low speed, adding 2 cups hot water (120° to 130°) into the dry ingredients.
Add Crisco also.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour and beat 2 more minutes.
With a spoon, mix in the rest of the flour and knead until smooth.
Let rise until doubled. Make into buns and bake at 375°.

title: chocolate raspberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. With mixer, beat cream cheese in a large bowl until fluffy; gradually add condensed milk and beat until smooth. Add egg, lemon juice and vanilla; mix well. Arrange raspberries on bottom of crust. Very slowly pour cream cheese mixture over berries. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until center is almost set. Cool.

title: banana-nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
In small bowl, mix 1/2 cup walnuts and 2 tablespoons oats; set aside.
Mix remaining nuts and oats with flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In another bowl, mash bananas.
Beat in milk, honey, melted butter and egg until blended.
Stir banana mixture into flour mixture just until blended.
Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon batter into muffin tins; sprinkle with nut-oat mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden and toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Immediately remove muffins from pan.
Serve warm or cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tortilla dip
directions: Mix all together. Refrigerate and serve with chips.

title: peanut butter lovers' popcorn
directions: Bring sugar and butter to a boil and boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over popped corn, stirring to coat all pieces well.

title: low calorie dilled carrots
directions: Combine onions, parsley, salt, pepper, dill and salad dressing.
Pour over carrots.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart dish, stir undiluted soup, mayo, eggs and onions until well blended.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: plenty for 20
directions: Brown meat.
Add celery and mushrooms.
Season to taste as desired.
Cook spaghetti.
Add meat mixture to spaghetti.
While hot, add chunks of cheese (entire package of cheese).
Mix until melted.
Add stewed tomatoes.
Mix.
Bake to heat and assure cheese all melted at about 350° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop your popcorn.
Pour into large baking dish.
Boil first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes, then add last 3 ingredients.
Pour your mixture over popcorn and work it all over real good until all is covered.
Bake in oven for about 10 to 15 minutes at 300°.
Stir around to cover all popcorn.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in chicken broth until very tender.
With potato masher, mash through mixture a couple of times to mash some of the potatoes.
Add meat and continue cooking on low heat, stirring occasionally while preparing white sauce.

title: cajun martini
directions: Slice pepper in half lengthwise without cutting stem and put in newly opened bottle of gin or vodka. Fill remaining airspace with vermouth and recap bottle. Refrigerate 8 to 16 hours.
Remove pepper and store bottle in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water until thick.
Heat soup and beat in cream cheese.
Add gelatine.
Cool in pan with cold water in the sink.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased mold and refrigerate.
Unmold and serve with soda crackers.

title: ann's black-eyed pea dip
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add tomato and cook until soft.
Add other ingredients.
Serve in chafing dish with tortilla chips.

title: microwave peanut brittle(yields 1 pound)
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, corn syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; mix well.
Microwave for 1 to 2 minutes; stir in soda until light and foamy.
Pour onto buttered baking sheet.
Let cool until firm.
Break into pieces.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Heat water and dissolve jello.
Put jello and all other ingredients in blender for a few seconds.
Let cool.

title: watercress and mushrooms in mustard dressing
directions: Rinse mushrooms and trim off most of stems.
Rinse watercress, drain and remove tough stems.
Chop green and white part of scallion.
Combine scallion with yogurt, mustard, capers, salt and pepper.
Spoon over watercress and mushrooms.

title: wheat germ muffins
directions: Mix well and set aside the biscuit mix, wheat germ and sugar. Cream peanut butter and egg and add water and vanilla.

title: chile con queso
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Melt cheese in double boiler and add all other ingredients.
Serve warm in chafing dish or fondue with corn chips.
Makes a lot.

title: tabouleh
directions: Soak bulghur wheat in 2 cups of warm water for 1/2 hour.
Chop parsley, green onions and tomatoes.
Pour excess water from wheat. Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaves or stuffed in pita pockets.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients in saucepan.
Let come to boil.
Stir often.
Set aside to cool.
Mix the pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine together well.
Press into a 10 x 6 1/2-inch baking dish.
Blend cheese and 1/2 cup sugar until fluffy.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Spread first mixture over all.
Chill several hours.

title: rhubarb-orange bread
directions: Cut orange rind very fine.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender; drain.
Add 3 tablespoons water and 1 cup sugar.
Boil until thick; set aside.
Combine buttermilk with remaining 1 cup sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder. Stir into egg mixture.
Stir in rhubarb and orange rind.
Pour into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken 'n rice casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and lay raw chicken on top.
Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: shirley's nutty pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pat in pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Blend cheese and 1 cup sugar. Add 1/2 package gelatin, which has been mixed with 2 tablespoons water.
Fold in topping and spread over cooled pretzel mix.
Mix strawberry gelatin and boiling water.
Stir in 1/2 package unflavored gelatin, which has been mixed with 2 tablespoons water. Add strawberries.
Let thicken or partially set.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and onion until done.
Drain.
Mix soups, add cheese, cook rice in microwave, then add to mixture and stir.
Top with cheese and crumbled crackers.
Bake until hot and cheese is melted.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
In a casserole dish layer ingredients, beginning with beans, 1/2 bottle of salsa, beef, remainder of salsa and chopped olives.
Cover top with sour cream and grated cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: linguine with mussels and red sauce
directions: Discard any open mussels; place remaining mussels in a large bowl.
Cover with cold water.
Sprinkle with cornmeal; let stand 30 minutes.
Drain and rinse mussels; set aside.
Discard cornmeal.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Pare thinly and remove eyes.
Shred enough potatoes to make 4 cups.
Drain potatoes thoroughly.
In a small mixer bowl, beat egg until thick and lemon colored.
Mix potatoes, onion, flour and salt.
Melt butter or oleo in a large skillet over low heat.
Shape potato mixture into 8 patties. Place in skillet.
Cook over medium heat, turning once, about 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Heat together in large saucepan the sugar, butter and water until butter is melted. Add chocolate chips and stir until smooth. Stir in eggs, then add dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°
until "most" centers of cookies have "dropped." Remove from oven at once and cool on racks.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the oil, 1 stick butter, water and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Have ready flour, sugar and soda.
Pour the boiled mixture over the dry mixture; mix quickly.
Add buttermilk, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour in a sheet cake pan, 11 x 16 inches.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Fry meat; break apart (drain grease).
Add all other ingredients.
Crush tortilla chips and mix with meat mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Top with grated cheese. Return to oven for 20 minutes.

title: homemade tomato catsup
directions: Cook until thick; stirring constantly.
It is easy to stick. Put in 3 pint jars and seal.
It is real good.

title: individual cheesecake
directions: Prepare muffin tins.
Put one vanilla wafer in bottom of each. Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg, lemon juice and vanilla together until creamy.
Spoon on top of each vanilla wafer.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: coq-au-vin
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in a bag.
Add chicken; shake to coat.
Set aside.
Meanwhile, cut bacon into 1-inch pieces; put bacon in skillet.
Fry lightly; do not drain.
Stir in flour from bag.
Add remaining ingredients; let simmer on low until done or bake in oven at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or 1 hour and 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Serves 6.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make patties and fry in hot Wesson oil.

title: streakless window cleaner
directions: In a one gallon container, pour ingredients.
Add water to fill container.

title: seafood strata
directions: Grease baking dish lightly.
Layer bread, cheese, seafood and more cheese (in that order).
Mix eggs, butter and milk and pour over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: squirrel fricassee
directions: Mix flour, salt
and
pepper
in
bowl.
Coat
squirrel pieces with seasoned flour.
In large frypan over medium heat, fry bacon until
grease
begins to collect.
Add squirrel meat and fry until well
browned
on	all
sides.
Add
onion
and chicken broth. Cover
and cook over medium heat for 1/2 hour. Reduce heat to low and
continue cooking for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat
is tender.
If desired, prepare gravy from pan drippings just before serving.
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions; drain.
Stir butter and Parmesan cheese into hot vermicelli.
Add eggs, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into 10-inch pie plate.

title: chunky potatoes
directions: Chop potatoes in small chunks, leaving the skins on.
Dot butter evenly on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt, pepper, bacon bits and shredded cheese.
Microwave covered casserole dish for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Cook rosamarina macaroni; set aside.
Drain fruit.
Combine syrup from fruit, flour and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil; add eggs.
Add fruit to macaroni.
Stir.
Add syrup.
Cool 3 to 4 hours.
Add Cool Whip.
Makes a large salad.

title: cream puffs
directions: Grease baking sheet.
Heat water, oleo and salt to a rolling boil.
Stir in flour all at once.
Continue to stir vigorously until mixture leaves sides of pan and makes a ball-like mass.
Cool until just warm.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Drop from tablespoon onto baking sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until brown and quite firm to touch.
Fill with Vanilla Pie Filling or ice cream.
Sift powdered sugar on top or spread with chocolate icing.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until soft, then beat potatoes and margarine well.
Take beater off and rinse to avoid potato string in mixture.
Do not scrape off.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook at 350° in preheated oven for 45 minutes, or until pie shakes slightly in middle.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Cook broccoli until nearly tender (fresh broccoli); drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Garnish if desired.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter. Add sugar, parsley, worcestershire sauce. Add soups. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours and pour over slice of French bread and shredded Swiss cheese.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Chex and stir until well covered.
Put sugar in clean paper sack.
Put Chex mix in and shake until covered.
Enjoy!!

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Can add a small amount of cooked hamburger to sauce.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix and spread on tortillas and roll up tight and cover well. Store in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours.
Cut in small slices and serve with picante sauce.

title: orange glazed raisin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 medium muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray or line with paper baking cups.
Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Add combined milk, oil, egg and grated orange peel; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove to wire rack.
In a small bowl, combine powdered sugar and orange juice.
Drizzle over slightly cooled muffins.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Add tea bags to
boiling
water.
Let
stand for 5 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: peach berry cobbler
directions: Turn above ingredients into a 2-quart baking dish.

title: overnight butterscotch rolls
directions: Use Bundt pan.
Plunk frozen rolls in pan the night before. Sprinkle rolls with pudding and cinnamon.
Melt margarine and stir in sugar and nuts.
Dribble over rolls.
Cover frozen rolls with foil.
Leave out on kitchen counter overnight.
(By morning the rolls should fill the pan!)
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 30 minutes.
(Remove foil for last 10 minutes of baking.)
Cool a few minutes and turn out on serving dish.
This is a wonderful breakfast to serve when you have overnight guests.
It is quick, easy, delicious and impossible to mess up.

title: cranberry upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 10-inch iron skillet.
Add 1 cup sugar; cook and stir 3 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Spoon cranberry sauce over butter mixture; sprinkle pecans over all. Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat egg yolks until foamy. Gradually add remaining sugar; beat well.
Blend in orange juice. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Carefully spoon over topping in skillet.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 5 minutes in skillet; invert onto large serving plate.
Serve warm.
Great dessert!

title: cheesy spinach pie
directions: Defrost and drain spinach.
Mix it in a bowl with egg and Ricotta.
Line bottom of 8 or 9-inch pie pan with Muenster cheese slices.
Spoon in spinach mixture.
Cover with remainder of Muenster slices.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until brown and bubbly.

title: strawberry or banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk thoroughly.
Mix in sour cream.

title: puppy chow
directions: In saucepan melt chocolate morsels and margarine over low heat. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
In large bowl pour mixture over Crispix cereal, gently tossing until coated.
Place confectioners sugar in gallon size storage bag.
Add coated cereal to sugar and close bag tightly.
Gently shake bag until cereal is thoroughly coated.
Store in airtight container. Refrigerate.
Serve in bowl.
Yields 8 cups.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Bring to a boil.
Dissolve jello in mixture and add Coke. Pour into bowl and refrigerate for 8 minutes.
Take out and add chipped cherries, nuts, cheese and pineapple.
Put back into refrigerator and let jell.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble raw hamburger in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Pour chopped onion on the hamburger, then add beans.
Next add the can of mushroom soup (don't dilute) and spread over top. Last, layer Tater Tots over top. Bake at 350° until done.

title: churros
directions: In saucepan, bring water, sugar and salt to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour all at once and heat until smooth.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until mixture is smooth.
Spoon into pastry bag with large star point.
Pipe 3-inch strips onto waxed paper or floured surface.
Add lemon peel to fat and heat to 375°. Fry a few at a time 3 to 4 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on towel and roll in sugar.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add jar of sauce; rinse out jar with 3/4 cup water.
Make with uncooked lasagna noodles.
Layer, starting with noodles, then sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered tightly with foil, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli and onion in skillet until tender. Add to cooked rice and soups.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Trim all visible fat from lean pork loin; cut pork in thin strips.
Saute in pan sprayed with cooking spray until golden brown.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Place in glass jar and shake until well mixed.
Pour into pan and cook until the sauce is clear and slightly thickened.
Add the meat.
Cook over low heat for about 1 hour.
About 5 minutes before serving, add the green pepper, onion and pineapple chunks.
Serve over rice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs, 1 stick melted butter and granulated sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine powdered sugar, pineapple juice and 1 stick melted butter.
Beat and spread over crust.
Slice bananas (rounds) over last layer.
Spread pineapple over all and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries, then drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: crab spread
directions: Using a mixer, combine everything except crab meat until well blended.
Fold in crab meat.
Add more catsup and/or horseradish to taste.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Simmer the chili sauce and jelly together, then add to hot dogs.
One recipe of sauce can cook up to 30 to 40 hot dogs.
Use mini hot dogs or regular hot dogs cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: aunt annie's mustard
directions: Mix all ingredients in double boiler and cook, stirring constantly until thick.
Store in refrigerator. Keeps indefinitely.

title: dipped peanut butter sandwich cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on half of the crackers; top with remaining crackers to make sandwiches.
Refrigerate.
In a double boiler over simmering water, melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth.
Dip sandwiches and place on waxed paper until chocolate hardens.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: microwave cream of broccoli soup
directions: Put onion and butter in 2 quart microwave safe bowl.
Cover loosely and microwave on high 5-6 minutes, stirring once until onions just begin to brown.
Stir in flour to make a smooth paste. Gradually stir in water until well blended, then the broccoli, bouillon granules and pepper.
Cover and microwave on high 10-12 minutes until broccoli is tender and soup is thickened.
Carefully stir in milk.
Serve hot.

title: chicken in wild rice
directions: Combine ingredients in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top (4 to 6 boneless chicken breasts).
Shake one package Lipton onion soup mix on top.
Cover with foil and put in 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle with paprika. Put back in oven at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken broccoli chowder
directions: Combine carrot, water, chicken, broth, broccoli, onion and salt in 4-quart saucepan or Dutch oven.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer about 10 minutes. Bring to a full rolling boil; gradually add oat flour, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese.
Cover; let stand 3 to 5 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle with Savory Add-A-Crunch to serve.
Makes about 4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.
Milk may be added if soup becomes too thick upon standing.

title: barbecups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown ground beef in a large skillet.
Drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Cook 1 minute to blend flavors, stirring constantly.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts and lemon rind. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: noodle kugel
directions: In large bowl, combine cooked noodles, sour cream, cottage cheese, eggs, sugar, butter and salt; mix well.
Stir in drained pineapple and raisins and turn mixture into greased two to three-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes six to eight servings.

title: cheese and egg casserole
directions: Soak bread in milk; drain after 5 minutes.
Save milk. Combine eggs, salt, pepper and milk.
Melt butter in pan and scramble the eggs, only until soft.
Add soaked bread cubes to eggs.
Mix.
Place in 9-inch square baking dish.
Spread cheese on egg mixture.
Sprinkle with cooked bacon.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: spinach salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, then drain on toweling and crumble. Break spinach into bite-sized pieces and chill until crisp.
Make dressing by combining bacon drippings, vinegars, garlic, oil, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Place crisp spinach leaves in a large salad bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add crumbled bacon and just enough dressing to coat each leaf lightly.
Store remaining dressing in the refrigerator.
Toss and serve at once. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rock-n-horse salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken quiche (quick & easy)
directions: Spray pan with non-stick spray.
Layer in the following order:
chicken, vegetable(s), cheese.
Pour batter over this. Cook for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: double chocolate layer cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer on medium speed until blended. Add eggs; mix. Stir the melted chocolate into 1 cup of the batter. Pour chocolate batter into the crust. Top with the plain batter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Makes 8 servings.

title: tammy's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and fresh garlic; drain.
Set aside. Make a double batch of Spatini tomato sauce following directions on box for tomato paste.
Season with oregano, basil and garlic powder to taste.
Boil lasagna until tender with a fork; drain. Combine the Ricotta cheese and the egg in a bowl.
Season with oregano.

title: easy vegetarian chili
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream and cheddar cheese, in a crock pot; stir to combine.
Place on low heat and cook 6 - 8 hours.
If pressed for time, cook on high heat for 2 hours.

title: citrus punch
directions: Stir juices with sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add ice. Garnish with slices.
Great thirst quencher on hot summer days!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and milk in saucepan and boil 2 minutes (or until sugar is dissolved).
Remove from heat; combine peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla in the same pan.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate about 30 minutes or until set.

title: kit-kat bars
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with crackers.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers. Layer 1 more time with crackers and pour remaining mixture over crackers.
Add 1 more layer of crackers.
Then melt last 3 ingredients.
Spread over top layer of crackers.
Refrigerate.

title: squash choco-chip cookies
directions: Mix together; stir in chips.
Drop on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: seafood scallop shells
directions: A perfect make ahead dish.
All ingredients can be combined, placed in shells and frozen without cooking, just thaw and bake.

title: tortilla roll-ups(appetizer)
directions: Drain all wet ingredients, then mix with other.
Spread on tortillas.
Wrap individually and chill for 2 hours.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: If using raw sweet potatoes, peel and cook first.
Mash sweet potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Make a ball of sweet potatoes in your hand and place a marshmallow in the middle.
Make sure marshmallow is covered with sweet potato, then roll in crushed cereal or chips.
Bake about 30 minutes in oven at 350° (marshmallows will disappear).

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix together the enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and soup.
Add hamburger.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread some sauce-hamburger mixture on bottom of pan.
Add tortilla chips.
Put rest of mixture on chips, making sure chips are coated well.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.	Pour
into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: cheese roll
directions: Combine grated cheese, garlic, onion and pecans.
Work together and roll into two rolls.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: chocolate graham cracker bars
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with graham crackers. In a saucepan, bring margarine, butter and brown sugar to a boil. Boil 2 minutes. Pour over crackers. Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and immediately spread chocolate chips. Cool and break into small pieces.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Layer vegetables and meat with onions on top.
Add tapioca, salt, sugar and tomato juice. Cook 2 1/2 hours, then stir and cook another 2 1/2 hours.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the beef, bread crumbs, onion, 1/2 teaspoon of the salt, 1/4 teaspoon of the pepper and the rice in a medium size bowl.
Mix together until well blended. Divide the mixture into balls and set aside.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Cream together the oil, eggs, vanilla, sugar and margarine. Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sponge cake layers
directions: Heat milk in small saucepan until bubbles form around edge of pan.
Remove from heat.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer at high speed, beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add the sugar, beating until the mixture is smooth and well blended, about 5 minutes.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture just until smooth.
Add warm milk and vanilla, beating just until combined.

Turn batter into an ungreased 9-inch round layer cake pan, an ungreased 8-inch round layer cake pan and an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan (pour slightly less batter into square pan). Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: eva's chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Mix egg and sugar; add melted chocolate.
Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake about 20 minutes at 400°.
Use a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt, shortening and boiling water all together until shortening melts.
Then add slightly beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast cakes in warm water and add to mixture.
Beat in approximately 7 cups flour until the right consistency (firm but sticky).
Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
(Will keep 2 to 3 days in refrigerator.) Make out in any form.
Let rise.
Bake at 400°.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix buttermilk, mayonnaise, sour cream and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing thoroughly.
Crumble cheeses and add to dressing mix. Chill thoroughly.

title: summer supper dessert
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press firmly into the bottom of the pan.
Refrigerate.
Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in a large bowl.
Stir in cold water. Refrigerate until slightly thickened.

Melt marshmallows in milk in saucepan on low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Cool completely. Arrange banana slices in single layer on crust. Stir whipped topping into marshmallow mixture.
Swirl slightly into gelatin to marbleize.
Pour over bananas.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with additional whipped topping, if desired.
Makes 20 servings.

title: fruit medley bowl
directions: Seed each fruit and cut in cubes or balls.
Prepare each fruit in a separate bowl; toss lightly with fruit fresh to preserve color.
When ready to serve, drain fruits, individually; then place all in a large bowl or watermelon rind.
Serve plain or with any fruit salad topping or dressing.
Serves 25 to 30 people. Will serve twice this amount at a reception.
Use 1/2 this amount for 5 quarts.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits, reserving 1 1/2 cups of pineapple and chunky fruit juice.
Cook pudding as directed on package using 1 1/2 cups fruit juice instead of milk.
Cool.
When cool, fold in fruit. Put in glass serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate fudge candy
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in a saucepan; heat and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook on low for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Pour into a buttered pan.

title: taco salad
directions: Wash lettuce; let drain.
Heat lg. skillet and add oil.
Saute meat; add salt and pepper, chili powder and cumin.	Cook meat until crumble, let meat drain.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook 5 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until blended.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased).
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: mud turtles
directions: Place all in saucepan; bring to rolling boil and let boil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes (not over).
While hot, stir in peanut butter and quick oats; stir and drop on wax paper.
Let cool and eat.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers finely.
Chop nuts and cut drained cherries in half.
Mix together in large bowl.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread up fine, add peas, corn, carrots, mushrooms, and onion.
Add cheese if desired.
Add enough mayonnaise to mix well.
Chill several hours before eating.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Heat milk and sugar until it boils, stirring constantly (about 7 minutes).
Cool well.
Add chocolate chips and butter.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased, glass casserole dish. Cut into squares when totally cool.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over lot heat, melt chips with salt and sweetened condensed milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and chopped nuts.
Line a 9-inch square pan with waxed paper.
Pour mixture onto wax paper and chill 2 hours.
Cut into squares and store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: cornbread
directions: Pour muffin mix in large bowl.
Stir until all lumps are gone. Add well beaten eggs, pouring a little at a time, stirring with large spoon.
Mix until it comes to a thin paste.
Add milk and water, stirring until mixture is well mixed.
Put Crisco and margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and place in hot oven (350°). Allow pan to become hot, then pour mixture into pan, stirring with the hot oil.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Wrap in foil or waxed paper until ready to serve.

title: spanish fudge
directions: In a large electric skillet, set at 280°, combine sugar, butter, cinnamon, salt and milk.
Bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn heat off and add remaining ingredients. Stir until well blended.
Pour into 8-inch buttered pan.
Cool before cutting.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Remove the outer leaves of the cabbage and rinse and dry it. Remove the core and grate the cabbage fine (this can be done in the food processor).

title: joanna's peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in sugar slowly.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Fold this mixture into the whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Garnish with chocolate syrup or chocolate curls if desired.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: chicken and garden vegetable twist
directions: In skillet, in hot oil, cook broccoli and carrots with basil and garlic powder until tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Add macaroni and chicken.
Heat through, stirring often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Melt margarine in water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour, stirring until you can form a ball.
Beat eggs into mixture one at a time.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400°
for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese to soften.
Gradually add milk to get a smooth consistency.
Stir in instant pudding and beat mixture together for 2 minutes.
Spread pudding mixture over cooled puff.
Top with a layer of whipped topping and fresh fruit or drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: classic waldorf salad
directions: Mix together:
mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Add to mixture the apples and celery.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine; stir cocoa until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese crock blend
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in Cheddar and Blue cheese.
Gradually beat in wine to make the spread creamy.
Add red pepper and stir in walnuts.
Pack into crocks or jars, cover tightly with plastic wrap or foil and refrigerate until serving time.
This spread is best if aged 4 to 5 days.
Let stand at room temperature 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with small thin slices of rye or French bread, crackers, toasted water biscuits or Scandinavian flatbread.
If warm canapes are desired, spread and place in oven until bubbly.
Decorate with walnut halves, if desired.
Makes 2 cups.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix tomatoes and lettuce.
Heat chili and add to lettuce; add cheese and stir.
Add taco chips just before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix the next 6 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and mayonnaise; pour over second layer.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: drop christmas cookies
directions: Cut up dates, cherries and pineapple until fine.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup flour over fruit and let stand overnight.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add to walnuts and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rosh hashanah honey cake
directions: Grease and line 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans with waxed paper; set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, allspice and salt.
In a small bowl, combine honey, orange concentrate, oil and coffee.
In a large bowl with electric mixer, beat eggs.
Add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in dry ingredients alternately with orange mixture. Fold in nuts.
Pour batter in prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 45 minutes or until done. Remove loaves.
Cool completely.
Remove waxed paper before serving.

title: new waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, gently toss together pineapple, apple, celery, grapes, walnuts and kiwi fruit.
In a small bowl, stir together the mayonnaise, yogurt and honey; fold gently into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill 2 to 24 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: *Can also use lobster or crab.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cook fruit and sugar. Combine flour, milk and sugar. Place 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish in a 350° oven until it melts.
Add flour mixture and fruit with juice. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix as written.
When stiff enough to handle, break off pieces of dough and pat flat; place on greased pan.
Bake slowly until brown around edges.
These are brittle.
If soft cakes are desired, add a little milk.
Bake at 325° to 350° depending on oven.

title: sliced cucumbers
directions: Mix altogether; pour over cucumbers.
A few slices of onion added makes it good.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add flour alternating.
Add one egg at a time, add whipping cream, beat until mixture looks beaten; add lemon extract.
Grease bottom, not sides, of tube pan, then flour.
Bake at 300 to 325 degrees for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together Ricotta cheese, spinach, Parmesan cheese and egg until well blended.
Layer 1 cup sauce, 3 noodles, 1 cup Ricotta cheese mixture and 3 Mozzarella cheese slices in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers twice.
Cover with foil.

title: sooper easy cheese dip
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients and mix well. Over medium heat, heat until smooth, stirring often.
Serve dip with corn chips or as a topper for French fried potatoes or potato skins.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix and cook, being careful not to over cook. Put mixture into homemade ice cream machine.

title: ritze
directions: Combine slightly softened ice cream, milk and pudding mix. Crumble Ritz crackers fine.
Make crust with crackers and melted margarine.
Reserve 1/2 cup of cracker mixture.
Pour ice cream mixture over crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 12 servings.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix corn bread with crumbs and add stock.
Beat eggs slightly. Add milk, salt and pepper.
Add to bread mixture.
Add chopped celery, poultry seasoning and chopped onion.
Bake in a well-greased pan at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all together for 4 minutes.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cut margarine into small pieces.
Add boiling water and oats, let stand 20 minutes; add other ingredients, beat, bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Use Broiled Icing on warm cake.
Then place back in oven until lightly browned.

title: bagna caulda(italian)
directions: Heat together oil, butter, anchovies and garlic.
Keep very hot and serve with veggies and bread to catch the drippings.

title: tourtiere(french-canadian meat pie)
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Brown beef and pork together; drain.
Combine meat, potatoes and seasoning.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Fill with meat mixture, top with crust.
Seal and make slits in top crust for steam.
Brush with beaten egg if desired.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
I sometimes use the filling in tart shells; cover with pastry. Served hot or cold.
Makes nice change from sausage rolls. Freezes well.

title: broccoli italian
directions: Partly defrost broccoli.
In a large skillet, heat the olive oil and butter.
Cut garlic clove in half and saute until golden. Remove the garlic and spread the broccoli in a single layer in the pan.
Saute, turning gently, for 10 minutes or until tender. Arrange in a flameproof serving dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and place under broiler for about 1 minute.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and dry jello until well blended.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
